1
00:00:00,560 --> 00:00:02,600
You’re breathing now. You’re okay… so I’m okay.

2
00:00:03,280 --> 00:00:06,600
See, I'm breathing too.

3
00:00:07,680 --> 00:00:09,080
Never again.

4
00:00:10,560 --> 00:00:12,200
I’m never letting you go again.

5
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:14,000
You idiot.

6
00:00:14,320 --> 00:00:18,240
That’s what happens when you act with no knowledge.

7
00:00:18,680 --> 00:00:20,880
Ateş is even more attached to that little snake now.

8
00:00:20,960 --> 00:00:23,320
He cares about her deeply.

9
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:25,360
I know, mother...

10
00:00:25,440 --> 00:00:27,280
just tell me what we’re going to do.

11
00:00:28,640 --> 00:00:30,400
We’ll get rid of Mercan...

12
00:00:31,040 --> 00:00:32,720
...but my way.

13
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:36,120
Any leads on who did it?

14
00:00:36,360 --> 00:00:37,960
You’ll know when we find out.

15
00:00:38,040 --> 00:00:42,800
Maybe I'm looking too far. Maybe the culprit is right under my nose.

16
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:45,280
Kidnapping someone,

17
00:00:46,160 --> 00:00:49,800
especially a woman, sounds more like your style than mine.

18
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:52,080
And Dad, don’t accuse him.

19
00:00:52,680 --> 00:00:54,320
If it weren’t for him, I’d be dead.

20
00:00:54,560 --> 00:00:57,120
Don’t fool yourself. Ateş would never look at you.

21
00:00:57,600 --> 00:01:00,360
Are you done? I’d like to read.

22
00:01:01,320 --> 00:01:02,840
I’m not done!

23
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:05,200
Enough lying in bed. Get up.

24
00:01:08,080 --> 00:01:09,800
Get up and be useful for once.

25
00:01:10,440 --> 00:01:13,520
Mother Müzeyyen, I'm warning you the last time.

26
00:01:14,360 --> 00:01:17,360
From now on, you don’t enter that room when I’m not there.

27
00:01:17,440 --> 00:01:19,960
You don’t talk to her.

28
00:01:21,160 --> 00:01:22,960
I told you we could’ve talked on the phone.

29
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:24,800
Why bring me here? Someone will see--

30
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:29,840
Let’s squeeze a little more…

31
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:36,120
You don’t even have the breath to kill Mercan, girl!

32
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:38,320
Mercan is the weakest link right now.

33
00:01:38,520 --> 00:01:43,320
Once she breaks, Haydar and Nermin will panic and drop their guard.

34
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:45,920
So let’s talk about how we’re going to finish Mercan.

35
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,760
-Then-- -(suddenly shouts) Enough!

36
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:07,480
MERCAN: Ateş?

37
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,600
Are you there?

38
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,360
MERCAN: I’m coming in.

39
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,760
Where are you, Ateş?

40
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:17,720
I hope you didn’t go after those men…

41
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:50,800
Reşat’s parents were on that human trafficking list tied to Haydar.

42
00:04:51,320 --> 00:04:53,200
When the boat sank, they drowned.

43
00:04:53,840 --> 00:04:55,160
It’s my fault.

44
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:58,480
I suspected he might be connected. I should’ve checked again.

45
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:01,320
But why try to kill Mercan?

46
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:03,240
Why not Haydar?

47
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:06,760
Something doesn’t add up.

48
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:12,000
Maybe it’s just a feeling, I don’t know.

49
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:15,200
We’ll understand once we get him talking.

50
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:17,600
But the guy’s clearly not mentally stable.

51
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:33,320
Well, well…

52
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:38,560
...fancy guests. What brings you here?

53
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:43,840
People like you don’t usually wander around these parts.

54
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:50,680
Anyone who comes here pays a price. No one enters without permission.

55
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,960
We’re looking for someone

56
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:58,040
Don't cause trouble.

57
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:02,640
Pay the entrance fee, and we won’t cause trouble for you. Got it?

58
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:19,800
Entrance fee, huh?

59
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:22,440
Like Crazy Dumrul…

60
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:34,120
Have you ever heard of Crazy Dumrul

61
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:36,560
who demanded money from people crossing the bridge?

62
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:41,160
What the hell are you talking about? Huh?

63
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:44,800
Phone, watch, money… whatever you’ve got, drop it!

64
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:48,200
Come over here. Take it yourself.

65
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:13,040
Morning workout.

66
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:15,760
Works for me.

67
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:18,760
What workout, man?

68
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:57,400
-Do you know Reşat? -No, man, I don’t know any Reşat.

69
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:03,240
Tell the truth!

70
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:10,120
Okay! Stop, bro! He hangs around here sometimes...

71
00:08:10,840 --> 00:08:12,360
...five kilometers ahead!

72
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:20,680
You okay?

73
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:22,600
Just a scratch.

74
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:25,920
You’re in trouble, I’m telling you. Mercan’s gonna make you answer for that.

75
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,280
Let’s go.

76
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:18,040
-Where is he? -I don't know.

77
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:45,000
Did you bring the money?

78
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:48,080
Did you mention this to anyone?

79
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:50,480
No.

80
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:52,720
Does anyone know you're here?

81
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:54,720
No. I promised.

82
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:57,240
So, I didn't tell anyone anything.

83
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:01,800
I have no time to lose. Give me my money right now.

84
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:09,600
Yes. Alright.

85
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:16,400
Mr. Ateş is nearby. He's coming towards here.

86
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:22,720
I thought you said you didn’t tell anyone?

87
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:25,760
Don’t make excuses just to avoid paying.

88
00:10:26,680 --> 00:10:28,040
I didn’t tell anyone anything.

89
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:30,360
Give me my money, or I’ll tell everyone everything.

90
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:47,920
Ugh, mom… why won’t you answer your phone?

91
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:53,560
If Ateş finds that man before she does…

92
00:10:54,680 --> 00:10:56,240
I’m done for.

93
00:10:57,720 --> 00:11:00,680
He’ll cut me out of his life.

94
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:06,000
I can’t live without him.

95
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:27,680
Everything could’ve been much better with you…

96
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:34,520
Why did you bring that girl into our lives?

97
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:44,240
It’s all because of her! She just won’t die!

98
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:56,600
Miss. Aslı?

99
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:01,480
How dare you come in without knocking!

100
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:06,080
I did knock, Miss. Aslı… Maybe you didn’t hear.

101
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:07,600
I brought your herbal tea…

102
00:12:07,680 --> 00:12:10,760
Get out! Get out now!

103
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:23,240
This house is driving me insane!

104
00:12:51,920 --> 00:12:54,200
What are you doing in my room? What do you want?

105
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:55,880
What do you even have that I’d want?

106
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:58,680
You’re all broke!

107
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:02,960
Isn't that why you latched onto Ateş?

108
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:05,240
It’s all about the money!

109
00:13:06,040 --> 00:13:08,240
Stop talking nonsense and get out of my room.

110
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:19,000
Even the junk you use to look pretty isn’t yours!

111
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:34,640
These rags aren’t yours either!

112
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:45,720
If you had any pride, you wouldn’t even live here!

113
00:13:48,280 --> 00:13:51,600
You’re in someone else’s room, living off pity.

114
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,840
No shame at all.

115
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:06,880
Get out of my room! And don’t touch my things again!

116
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:09,880
I’ll do whatever I want!

117
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:15,280
I’ll rip off your mask! Your innocent act doesn’t work on me.

118
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:18,920
Everyone will see what a snake you really are!

119
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:26,400
You’re sick. A pathetic sick girl.

120
00:14:27,560 --> 00:14:30,600
I’ll never let you take root in Ateş’s life!

121
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:34,440
You’ve done everything you could for his money.

122
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:36,680
You used his kindness for your own gain.

123
00:14:37,280 --> 00:14:38,560
But it’s useless.

124
00:14:38,720 --> 00:14:42,520
Never... he’ll never love you.

125
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:52,000
They’ve completely lost it.

126
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:33,120
He’s freshly dead… still warm.

127
00:15:43,320 --> 00:15:45,440
Looks like he shot himself.

128
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:49,000
Seems that way. Damn it… this is bad.

129
00:15:51,920 --> 00:15:54,360
We didn’t even get to question him. Damn it!

130
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:56,760
This is bad… really bad.

131
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:59,760
What do we do with this?

132
00:16:02,320 --> 00:16:03,920
Call the police. Report it.

133
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:40,440
Hello, brother… I need money urgently.

134
00:16:41,080 --> 00:16:44,480
Mm‑hmm... can you lend me something?

135
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:47,440
It’s a family matter, bro.

136
00:16:47,800 --> 00:16:50,760
I wouldn’t ask if it wasn’t serious.

137
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:56,480
Mm‑hmm. I swear I’ll pay you back in two months max.

138
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:59,000
Maybe even sooner.

139
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:01,720
It won't even take two months.

140
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:05,680
We’re getting paid regularly now. No problem with that.

141
00:17:07,080 --> 00:17:09,120
Okay, I had some issues, but that’s over.

142
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:11,840
Fine, maybe it was late sometimes. But didn’t I always pay?

143
00:17:15,680 --> 00:17:17,760
Only a thousand left?

144
00:17:19,280 --> 00:17:22,640
I forgot, man. I'm sorry, brother.

145
00:17:25,480 --> 00:17:27,040
Fine… I get it. It’s okay.

146
00:17:27,280 --> 00:17:30,800
Just send me your IBAN. I don’t stay in debt to anyone.

147
00:17:32,120 --> 00:17:33,720
Thank you, bro.

148
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:46,320
This Berat...

149
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:50,480
He might be useful, especially now that he needs money.

150
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,720
We'll see.

151
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,560
Everything has its time.

152
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:12,400
He’s whining about a thousand… clown.

153
00:18:13,680 --> 00:18:16,720
One day it’ll be my turn. You’ll all see.

154
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:21,120
What is it, Nezir?

155
00:18:23,040 --> 00:18:27,200
-What? -What did he say, Haydar?

156
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:30,600
The man who kidnapped Mercan was found dead.

157
00:18:31,600 --> 00:18:33,520
Ateş found the body.

158
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:35,600
He’s always one step ahead! Always!

159
00:18:44,880 --> 00:18:46,480
You found the guy?

160
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:50,680
I did.

161
00:18:50,840 --> 00:18:53,280
Mercan was kidnapped because of your dirty business.

162
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:56,520
I don’t have any dirty business. It was all lies.

163
00:18:57,600 --> 00:18:59,560
Don’t lie.

164
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:02,120
She nearly died because of you.

165
00:19:03,080 --> 00:19:06,080
Have a little dignity and own up to it.

166
00:19:08,320 --> 00:19:11,240
I won’t tell Mercan. I don’t want to upset her any more.

167
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:13,800
She’s suffered enough.

168
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:16,760
She doesn’t need this too.

169
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:22,640
What’s going on? Is something wrong?

170
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:24,360
No, nothing.

171
00:19:24,880 --> 00:19:26,680
Nothing, sweetheart.

172
00:19:27,320 --> 00:19:31,080
Ateş found the guy... he was just telling us.

173
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:39,000
What happened to you two?

174
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:44,560
Shall we go, Haydar?

175
00:19:52,520 --> 00:19:54,280
Are you okay? Are you hurt?

176
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:56,680
We're fine.

177
00:19:58,560 --> 00:20:00,000
Look at you!

178
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:06,000
Your hand’s hurt.

179
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:10,840
Told you so.

180
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:13,920
Good luck explaining that to Mercan. I’m out.

181
00:20:15,760 --> 00:20:17,960
Why do you keep putting yourself in danger?

182
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:22,120
Drop it. I’m fine. It’s over.

183
00:20:22,920 --> 00:20:24,640
But what if something happens to you?

184
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:28,320
What do you expect me to do...

185
00:20:28,720 --> 00:20:30,880
sit and wait for them to come to me?

186
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:33,000
I don’t expect anything.

187
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:35,320
Just don’t hurt yourself.

188
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:38,720
If I have to, I will. You almost died.

189
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:46,720
And so what?

190
00:20:50,640 --> 00:20:52,400
What if something happens to me?

191
00:20:55,440 --> 00:21:01,200
Anyone who tries to hurt Ateş Karahan’s wife… pays the price.

192
00:21:03,960 --> 00:21:06,800
Is that what this is about? Ateş Karahan’s wife?

193
00:21:07,560 --> 00:21:09,080
That’s right.

194
00:21:09,960 --> 00:21:12,360
Fine. Is it over now?

195
00:21:17,240 --> 00:21:19,160
We found one dead.

196
00:21:19,880 --> 00:21:21,600
The other escaped.

197
00:21:23,360 --> 00:21:25,360
Until we catch him, it’s over for now.

198
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:29,720
You don’t need to be afraid anymore.

199
00:21:36,320 --> 00:21:37,840
Let me see your hand.

200
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:40,160
I said, it’s not important.

201
00:21:42,840 --> 00:21:44,480
Still. I want to see it.

202
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:55,520
Come on. Let’s take care of this upstairs.

203
00:21:56,320 --> 00:21:58,200
Come on.

204
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:41,360
Did you find the man?

205
00:22:41,480 --> 00:22:43,960
We did… He’s dead.

206
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:47,080
Thank God… We’re saved.

207
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:52,160
Aslı, Ateş doesn’t look like he’ll drop this easily.

208
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:54,840
He almost found the man before I did today.

209
00:22:55,560 --> 00:22:58,200
But he’s dead now, so it’s over.

210
00:22:59,560 --> 00:23:02,200
I’m telling you so you don’t pull another stupid stunt.

211
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:05,760
Fine, mom. Don’t start again.

212
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:08,360
What do we do now?

213
00:23:10,080 --> 00:23:13,200
We shake his trust in Mercan. That'll be our only move.

214
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:18,320
Mom, don’t you see? Ateş dotes on Mercan.

215
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:21,400
He said, "Mercan won’t be part of the revenge plan."

216
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:24,040
That girl planted discord in my family.

217
00:23:24,480 --> 00:23:27,480
Because of her, Ateş declared war on me…

218
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:30,040
You think I’ll let her get away with that?

219
00:23:31,520 --> 00:23:33,000
I have a few ideas.

220
00:23:33,760 --> 00:23:35,680
First, I need to talk to Nezir.

221
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:47,640
Come over.

222
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:52,800
Sit on the bed.

223
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:21,680
Come on, give me your hand.

224
00:24:40,120 --> 00:24:44,320
I’m not used to you doing what I say without arguing.

225
00:24:44,880 --> 00:24:46,040
That’s why I laughed.

226
00:24:47,760 --> 00:24:49,200
You’re getting spoiled again.

227
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:55,040
We need to clean this right away.

228
00:24:58,800 --> 00:25:02,960
Ugh... I wish you’d take care of yourself a little.

229
00:25:03,600 --> 00:25:06,000
You throw yourself into danger without blinking.

230
00:25:09,320 --> 00:25:13,440
This isn’t my first injury. It’s nothing.

231
00:25:14,760 --> 00:25:16,360
It’s not the first...

232
00:25:20,560 --> 00:25:22,680
but what if you’d run into that man?

233
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:27,880
God forbid, he could’ve hurt you too.

234
00:25:29,240 --> 00:25:31,560
I’m mad I couldn’t catch him alive.

235
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:36,480
I can’t believe you. Listen to what you’re still saying..

236
00:25:38,880 --> 00:25:41,000
What now? What is it?

237
00:25:47,600 --> 00:25:49,320
They tried to kill me.

238
00:25:49,600 --> 00:25:51,200
These people are dangerous.

239
00:25:51,280 --> 00:25:53,720
Why don't you get it? Why won’t you listen?

240
00:25:57,200 --> 00:25:59,120
It’s fine. There's nothing.

241
00:26:01,800 --> 00:26:03,360
What I lived through wasn’t a game…

242
00:26:04,240 --> 00:26:06,360
I’m scared to close my eyes and fall asleep.

243
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:10,240
Those moments, those faces… they’re still right in front of me.

244
00:26:14,840 --> 00:26:16,000
I’m right by you.

245
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:19,240
Okay, I’m fine.

246
00:26:22,360 --> 00:26:24,840
See? I’m right here. Nothing happened. Calm down.

247
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:27,120
But something could’ve happened.

248
00:26:27,240 --> 00:26:30,240
Why don’t you take me seriously? Why don't you listen?

249
00:26:30,920 --> 00:26:33,040
I know it wasn’t a game.

250
00:26:33,920 --> 00:26:35,320
And it’s normal to be scared.

251
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:37,800
It won’t happen again.

252
00:26:39,120 --> 00:26:41,000
No one will ever touch you again.

253
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:44,120
You still don’t get it.

254
00:26:47,800 --> 00:26:50,280
I’m not only scared for myself.

255
00:26:51,920 --> 00:26:53,280
Look, you’re hurt too.

256
00:26:59,480 --> 00:27:02,000
You’re right. I’m sorry.

257
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:08,400
I’ll be careful.

258
00:27:11,480 --> 00:27:12,480
Please be.

259
00:27:20,040 --> 00:27:22,880
I’ve been so emotional lately. I’m sorry.

260
00:27:25,120 --> 00:27:27,160
I think I’m overwhelmed.

261
00:27:28,880 --> 00:27:30,800
I hope I’m not overwhelming you as well.

262
00:27:32,920 --> 00:27:36,360
No. You’re not.

263
00:27:38,960 --> 00:27:40,400
Come on. I’m taking you somewhere.

264
00:27:40,480 --> 00:27:41,840
Now?

265
00:27:45,240 --> 00:27:47,960
-Where? -It’s a surprise. Come on.

266
00:27:50,400 --> 00:27:52,480
Should I bring the first aid kit too?

267
00:27:52,880 --> 00:27:55,320
Danger seems to follow you everywhere.

268
00:27:56,520 --> 00:27:58,680
Enough talking. Let’s go.

269
00:28:17,200 --> 00:28:18,520
Malik?

270
00:28:19,120 --> 00:28:21,200
Hey. You’re lost in thought…

271
00:28:22,520 --> 00:28:25,000
A piece of advice from me... don’t dive too deep, Malik.

272
00:28:25,080 --> 00:28:26,960
You’ll suffer for it.

273
00:28:30,240 --> 00:28:31,480
Are you okay, Malik?

274
00:28:32,280 --> 00:28:33,840
MALIK: No, Mr. Cemal.

275
00:28:34,600 --> 00:28:36,040
Not even close.

276
00:28:38,840 --> 00:28:40,680
Looks like the issue is quite big.

277
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:43,320
Is it about Çiçek?

278
00:28:47,760 --> 00:28:50,400
Don't look at me like that. I saw you talking.

279
00:28:51,040 --> 00:28:54,600
-We talk sometimes, that’s all. -Sure, you do.

280
00:28:56,120 --> 00:28:58,200
Malik, I know a thing or two about this stuff.

281
00:28:59,400 --> 00:29:01,080
I saw the way you look at each other.

282
00:29:01,960 --> 00:29:03,920
Your love is written all over your faces.

283
00:29:04,960 --> 00:29:06,520
You think so?

284
00:29:07,360 --> 00:29:09,200
More than that.

285
00:29:10,440 --> 00:29:13,320
So what’s the problem? Anything I can help with?

286
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:17,720
I wish, Mr. Cemal.

287
00:29:19,280 --> 00:29:21,040
There are big obstacles between us…

288
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:23,480
not easy to overcome.

289
00:29:24,480 --> 00:29:25,760
Too difficult.

290
00:29:28,480 --> 00:29:29,680
I get you, Malik.

291
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:31,720
I really do.

292
00:29:33,200 --> 00:29:34,480
Listen to me.

293
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:38,440
In Adana we say...

294
00:29:39,080 --> 00:29:41,200
...the bigger the love, the bigger the trouble.

295
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:44,600
Also, love doesn’t grow without hardship. Does it, Malik?

296
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:51,120
So no matter what happens, be patient and keep fighting.

297
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:55,920
I fight Mr. Cemal…

298
00:29:56,760 --> 00:30:02,920
but sometimes the people standing in your way tie your hands completely.

299
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:05,160
I'm exactly in that situation.

300
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:09,080
Look, you’re a lucky man, Malik.

301
00:30:10,080 --> 00:30:12,120
Because the woman you love loves you back.

302
00:30:14,280 --> 00:30:17,880
If it were one sided, I’d understand your hopelessness.

303
00:30:20,280 --> 00:30:22,160
But I don't think there can be any obstacles

304
00:30:22,240 --> 00:30:23,640
when you two stand together.

305
00:30:24,520 --> 00:30:26,320
Night always turns to morning.

306
00:30:27,880 --> 00:30:29,600
No matter what happens, just be patient.

307
00:30:29,680 --> 00:30:31,080
Keep fighting.

308
00:30:38,400 --> 00:30:40,840
-Thank you, Mr. Cemal. -See you, Malik.

309
00:31:00,160 --> 00:31:02,960
…that’s life… it just comes and goes…

310
00:31:03,040 --> 00:31:05,480
-Okay, please sit down. -Thank you, dear.

311
00:31:09,360 --> 00:31:12,160
Thank you, dear.

312
00:31:13,160 --> 00:31:14,600
Thank you, love.

313
00:31:29,600 --> 00:31:31,560
Sorry for dropping by unannounced…

314
00:31:31,920 --> 00:31:34,440
Don’t say that, son.

315
00:31:34,680 --> 00:31:36,480
This is your home too.

316
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:39,080
Come over

317
00:31:39,160 --> 00:31:41,320
anytime you wish.

318
00:31:42,280 --> 00:31:44,160
You did well to come.

319
00:31:44,480 --> 00:31:48,440
Stop by once in a while so the house feels lively again.

320
00:31:57,040 --> 00:32:00,960
Hopefully soon you’ll have a child too…

321
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:03,960
you’ll bring our grandchild to visit.

322
00:32:04,920 --> 00:32:06,840
Of course, that'll happen. Inshallah.

323
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:08,880
Inshallah. Inshallah.

324
00:32:14,200 --> 00:32:16,720
Güllü, let's prepare something to eat.

325
00:32:16,800 --> 00:32:18,360
These kids must have been hungry.

326
00:32:18,480 --> 00:32:20,040
Please don’t trouble yourselves.

327
00:32:20,360 --> 00:32:22,880
Come on, guests aren’t trouble, dear.

328
00:32:23,680 --> 00:32:26,520
Then... let us prepare something.

329
00:32:26,600 --> 00:32:27,920
You're not well.

330
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:29,200
You'd better rest.

331
00:32:29,480 --> 00:32:30,960
If this is our home too,

332
00:32:31,200 --> 00:32:32,640
then it’s no trouble.

333
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:37,440
Good, then.

334
00:32:37,600 --> 00:32:39,880
Dinner is on you two tonight.

335
00:32:43,400 --> 00:32:45,560
My wife’s been sick for two days

336
00:32:45,640 --> 00:32:48,760
I’ve been handling things. It’s good timing.

337
00:32:55,080 --> 00:32:59,440
Durmuş made quite a mess… sorry.

338
00:32:59,560 --> 00:33:01,200
It’s fine. We’ll take care of it.

339
00:33:14,680 --> 00:33:16,960
Çiçek. Where are you going?

340
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:20,960
I… um… I...

341
00:33:21,760 --> 00:33:24,080
Don’t disappear.

342
00:33:24,960 --> 00:33:26,320
Now go to the mansion.

343
00:33:26,840 --> 00:33:30,720
Collect the laundry, then go upstairs. Check if there’s anything else.

344
00:33:30,840 --> 00:33:32,920
And my eyes are on you. Remember that.

345
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:35,960
There’s nothing in the mansion, Mom.

346
00:33:36,160 --> 00:33:39,080
While tidying Mercan's room, I cleaned all the other rooms.

347
00:33:39,360 --> 00:33:41,560
Doesn't matter, check upstairs again.

348
00:33:41,640 --> 00:33:42,880
Just take a look around.

349
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:45,200
Something might turn up. Come on, girl. Come on.

350
00:33:45,280 --> 00:33:46,600
Fine…

351
00:33:54,520 --> 00:33:55,840
This won’t do.

352
00:33:56,560 --> 00:33:57,880
They’re always glued together.

353
00:33:59,040 --> 00:34:00,680
Malik Effendi, one way or another,

354
00:34:00,880 --> 00:34:03,520
I’ll show you what it's like talking to my daughter.

355
00:34:05,040 --> 00:34:06,680
You'll learn how to stay away from her.

356
00:34:41,400 --> 00:34:43,640
Let’s divide the work.

357
00:34:43,920 --> 00:34:46,840
I’ll do the dishes, you put things away.

358
00:34:47,120 --> 00:34:48,760
Then we’ll cook.

359
00:34:48,960 --> 00:34:50,240
-Okay.-Okay.

360
00:35:29,240 --> 00:35:30,640
Thanks.

361
00:35:55,200 --> 00:35:57,200
Who would’ve thought the great boss Ateş Karahan

362
00:35:57,640 --> 00:36:00,320
would be this good at housework?

363
00:36:03,680 --> 00:36:06,000
Life teaches you to survive.

364
00:36:06,760 --> 00:36:09,800
I’ve handled my own chores most of my life,

365
00:36:10,200 --> 00:36:11,880
even in university.

366
00:36:12,680 --> 00:36:15,440
So, kitchens aren’t foreign to me.

367
00:36:17,600 --> 00:36:20,440
I wasn’t born with a silver spoon like you, ma’am.

368
00:36:22,440 --> 00:36:23,720
Look at you.

369
00:36:24,160 --> 00:36:27,520
If they didn’t let me do anything, is that my fault?

370
00:36:27,760 --> 00:36:29,200
Convenient for you though.

371
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:31,440
Come on, wash those.

372
00:36:32,520 --> 00:36:34,080
Alright, I'm washing.

373
00:36:34,280 --> 00:36:36,000
See? They’re clean.

374
00:36:36,080 --> 00:36:37,880
Stop talking and wash properly.

375
00:36:38,320 --> 00:36:39,640
Make it really soapy.

376
00:36:40,480 --> 00:36:43,600
Help instead of staring.

377
00:36:44,320 --> 00:36:46,680
Are you giving me the plates or not?

378
00:36:49,880 --> 00:36:52,160
Come on, already!

379
00:36:56,120 --> 00:37:00,400
See what you did? It broke because of you.

380
00:37:00,960 --> 00:37:02,160
Because of me?

381
00:37:02,400 --> 00:37:03,600
Leave it, I’ll clean it.

382
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:05,320
All because of me. Right.

383
00:37:05,480 --> 00:37:06,760
No, I’ll do it.

384
00:37:07,080 --> 00:37:08,560
You’ll cut your hand.

385
00:37:08,640 --> 00:37:10,960
-It’s already injured. -I said, leave it.

386
00:37:12,040 --> 00:37:13,760
You’re pretty clumsy yourself.

387
00:37:14,360 --> 00:37:16,040
One injured person at home is enough.

388
00:37:18,840 --> 00:37:20,160
Go back to your dishes.

389
00:37:47,720 --> 00:37:49,720
After we clean up, we should go shopping.

390
00:37:49,800 --> 00:37:51,440
There's nothing left in the fridge.

391
00:37:51,520 --> 00:37:53,360
Mm‑hmm. Okay.

392
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:22,560
It won't disturb you now.

393
00:38:25,760 --> 00:38:27,040
Thank you.

394
00:38:33,160 --> 00:38:34,480
To me?

395
00:38:34,600 --> 00:38:36,000
You asked for this war.

396
00:38:36,080 --> 00:38:37,760
Here!

397
00:39:26,280 --> 00:39:31,000
Um... If we keep fooling around,

398
00:39:31,400 --> 00:39:34,320
nothing will get done.

399
00:39:35,560 --> 00:39:38,680
In the meantime, who’s cooking?

400
00:39:39,680 --> 00:39:42,360
because, I don’t really know how.

401
00:39:45,920 --> 00:39:49,200
I’ll cook. You’ll help.

402
00:39:53,840 --> 00:39:58,440
By the way, didn’t you make pastries the other day?

403
00:39:59,600 --> 00:40:04,520
Or were you pretending not to know so I’d do everything?

404
00:40:06,840 --> 00:40:08,800
I had help, then…

405
00:40:22,160 --> 00:40:23,760
You should do that more often.

406
00:40:24,280 --> 00:40:25,760
What?

407
00:40:26,520 --> 00:40:28,240
Laugh. With joy.

408
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:35,920
You’re always so serious…

409
00:40:36,600 --> 00:40:38,800
seeing you loosen up is nice.

410
00:41:12,200 --> 00:41:13,520
No coffee for me?

411
00:41:15,920 --> 00:41:20,920
Didn’t think you’d want one.

412
00:41:27,160 --> 00:41:29,040
Burak? Come look at this.

413
00:41:29,160 --> 00:41:31,360
I made a few improvements to speed up things.

414
00:41:32,680 --> 00:41:37,520
I have things to finish. Is it okay if I look later?

415
00:41:37,760 --> 00:41:41,600
It’ll take one minute. Please, let me know what you think.

416
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:50,720
Are you okay? You seem down.

417
00:41:51,640 --> 00:41:55,680
I’m fine. Too busy with the work.

418
00:41:56,080 --> 00:41:58,040
Just stressed with deadlines.

419
00:42:00,400 --> 00:42:02,080
What did you want to show me?

420
00:42:02,240 --> 00:42:04,480
Never mind. Go back to your work.

421
00:42:05,920 --> 00:42:07,440
I’ll get myself a coffee.

422
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:10,120
You know, since I always drink coffee at this hour.

423
00:42:16,280 --> 00:42:18,600
They keep telling me to read books…

424
00:42:18,720 --> 00:42:20,800
I read and read, but nothing changes.

425
00:42:29,200 --> 00:42:32,640
You should see how happy they are.

426
00:42:33,040 --> 00:42:34,880
That mansion isn’t good for them at all.

427
00:42:34,960 --> 00:42:38,120
There are so many people around them.

428
00:42:39,000 --> 00:42:41,200
Their staff do all their work.

429
00:42:42,120 --> 00:42:44,600
At least Mrs. Müzeyyen isn’t around.

430
00:42:45,080 --> 00:42:47,640
These kids have it tough. Really tough.

431
00:42:47,760 --> 00:42:49,560
Tell me about it. Exactly.

432
00:42:49,800 --> 00:42:52,440
She’s bad… and so is her daughter.

433
00:42:58,880 --> 00:43:00,120
The kitchen’s done.

434
00:43:00,480 --> 00:43:02,960
-Thank you. -Thank you, dear.

435
00:43:03,600 --> 00:43:05,520
We’re going shopping.

436
00:43:05,800 --> 00:43:07,200
We’ll be back shortly.

437
00:43:09,760 --> 00:43:11,120
You didn’t have to, son.

438
00:43:11,440 --> 00:43:12,680
We could've managed it.

439
00:43:12,800 --> 00:43:15,680
Let them go, dear. Let them walk around a bit.

440
00:43:16,680 --> 00:43:18,600
Don’t interfere.

441
00:43:21,160 --> 00:43:22,960
So, did you make a list?

442
00:43:24,600 --> 00:43:26,840
No need. We remember everything.

443
00:43:29,640 --> 00:43:32,320
Lists matter, son. Even in marriage.

444
00:43:32,480 --> 00:43:37,760
Don't stop thinking about the shopping list in your marriage.

445
00:43:38,400 --> 00:43:41,120
Marriage is like a meal, in a way.

446
00:43:42,640 --> 00:43:46,840
Just like we pay attention to the salt and sugar in a meal,

447
00:43:47,160 --> 00:43:49,200
we must pay attention in marriage too.

448
00:43:50,400 --> 00:43:53,840
Good words, small surprises...

449
00:43:54,000 --> 00:43:56,400
...they’re like salt and sugar.

450
00:43:57,200 --> 00:43:59,680
Your manners are like spices.

451
00:44:00,640 --> 00:44:05,000
They add color and flavor.

452
00:44:06,800 --> 00:44:08,920
If you don’t ruin the recipe…

453
00:44:09,080 --> 00:44:13,120
the taste will be perfect. Period.

454
00:44:16,080 --> 00:44:18,080
-Let’s go. -Alright.

455
00:44:26,600 --> 00:44:30,160
These need to breathe a little.

456
00:44:31,760 --> 00:44:33,360
Look, I'll tell you something.

457
00:44:33,440 --> 00:44:38,560
Now that you're feeling better, let’s go out and walk around together.

458
00:44:39,200 --> 00:44:41,040
Okay?

459
00:45:04,800 --> 00:45:07,000
Çiçek! Çiçek! Where are you going?

460
00:45:23,720 --> 00:45:25,240
Come back home, dear.

461
00:45:29,400 --> 00:45:30,920
Mom… please.

462
00:45:31,520 --> 00:45:33,680
We’re not doing anything wrong.

463
00:45:37,480 --> 00:45:39,280
Malik is such a good person.

464
00:45:45,440 --> 00:45:48,000
I said go home, daughter!

465
00:45:55,680 --> 00:45:58,280
Are you really going to walk over your own mother for some man?

466
00:45:59,880 --> 00:46:01,880
Mom… why are you so harsh?

467
00:46:02,080 --> 00:46:04,960
We love each other.

468
00:46:05,680 --> 00:46:07,400
Enough! I don’t want to hear it, Çiçek!

469
00:46:07,760 --> 00:46:10,520
One day love ends…

470
00:46:10,800 --> 00:46:13,440
and all that’s left is pain and regret.

471
00:46:14,200 --> 00:46:17,880
Nothing in life is guaranteed…

472
00:46:18,400 --> 00:46:21,800
Even if I married someone else, the same things could happen.

473
00:46:22,320 --> 00:46:25,920
If you walk out that door… you walk over me.

474
00:46:26,640 --> 00:46:29,040
And a child who ignores her mother is no child of mine.

475
00:46:29,120 --> 00:46:31,440
I won’t even look at your face again. Do you understand?

476
00:46:33,600 --> 00:46:35,280
Mom… please…

477
00:46:36,840 --> 00:46:38,360
It’s Malik or me.

478
00:46:39,840 --> 00:46:43,560
If you go, don’t come back, Çiçek.

479
00:47:09,080 --> 00:47:10,760
Good thing we came here.

480
00:47:12,600 --> 00:47:13,640
Thank you.

481
00:47:15,360 --> 00:47:16,800
For what?

482
00:47:18,200 --> 00:47:19,680
For bringing me here.

483
00:47:22,040 --> 00:47:24,000
I wanted you to relax a little.

484
00:47:51,960 --> 00:47:53,440
Are you okay?

485
00:48:01,040 --> 00:48:07,600
I… thought someone was following us.

486
00:48:11,800 --> 00:48:14,840
I’m here. Right beside you.

487
00:48:15,600 --> 00:48:17,240
There’s nothing to be afraid of.

488
00:48:19,200 --> 00:48:21,640
If anything, they should be afraid of you.

489
00:48:23,520 --> 00:48:26,280
Come on, let’s focus. Hope we don’t forget anything.

490
00:48:27,920 --> 00:48:32,840
We shouldn’t. You bragged that "everything’s in my head."

491
00:48:50,440 --> 00:48:51,920
Smiling suits you.

492
00:49:04,000 --> 00:49:08,320
I mean… smiling is good for you.

493
00:49:09,240 --> 00:49:11,200
Let's go.

494
00:49:51,960 --> 00:49:54,240
Well, well… Mrs. Müzeyyen.

495
00:49:54,760 --> 00:49:55,960
What an honor.

496
00:49:57,400 --> 00:49:59,400
You didn’t tell me your mother was coming, Aslı.

497
00:50:02,760 --> 00:50:05,200
We’re not here to chat.

498
00:50:06,560 --> 00:50:09,560
You’re the last person I’d want to chat with, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

499
00:50:10,480 --> 00:50:12,120
I have an offer for you.

500
00:50:18,000 --> 00:50:19,280
Do you want Mercan?

501
00:50:20,680 --> 00:50:22,240
More than anything.

502
00:50:26,760 --> 00:50:28,240
What would you do for her?

503
00:50:28,520 --> 00:50:30,240
Whatever it takes.

504
00:50:30,680 --> 00:50:32,160
I'd even give my life.

505
00:50:32,280 --> 00:50:35,000
I don’t understand what you all see in that simple girl!

506
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:38,680
Aslı!

507
00:50:39,200 --> 00:50:41,200
So, you'd risk your life?

508
00:50:42,200 --> 00:50:45,040
Do you have that kind of courage?

509
00:50:49,480 --> 00:50:50,840
Do you think I have?

510
00:50:57,440 --> 00:50:59,880
You should’ve given me a couple of the bags to carry.

511
00:51:00,000 --> 00:51:01,160
No need. I'll carry them.

512
00:51:05,440 --> 00:51:08,880
Oh, there’s a place selling organic food…

513
00:51:09,160 --> 00:51:10,840
Should we get something for the mansion?

514
00:51:12,240 --> 00:51:14,880
Go ahead, I’m right here.

515
00:51:15,240 --> 00:51:17,200
Come on, you too.

516
00:51:37,040 --> 00:51:38,040
PHOTOGRAPHER: Excuse me.

517
00:51:38,920 --> 00:51:40,880
How about a nice memorial photo?

518
00:51:41,040 --> 00:51:43,880
Something you can show your grandkids one day.

519
00:51:49,680 --> 00:51:51,000
I don’t know…

520
00:52:01,000 --> 00:52:03,800
No need. We’re in a hurry. Thank you.

521
00:52:04,640 --> 00:52:05,880
Come on, help me out.

522
00:52:06,040 --> 00:52:07,680
I haven’t made a single sale today.

523
00:52:09,640 --> 00:52:14,560
Well, if you haven’t... okay then.

524
00:52:14,960 --> 00:52:17,160
Thank you, brother. Let me take your bags away.

525
00:52:20,120 --> 00:52:23,040
I'm putting them here. It’s a shop I know. Nothing will happen.

526
00:52:23,920 --> 00:52:26,000
Let me take your purse, as well.

527
00:52:30,120 --> 00:52:31,520
I’ll take a photo so good

528
00:52:31,640 --> 00:52:34,280
you’ll hang it in your living room for years.

529
00:52:35,320 --> 00:52:36,840
Take it, then.

530
00:52:46,480 --> 00:52:49,000
Ready… I’m taking it. Took it.

531
00:53:05,880 --> 00:53:07,800
Can you get closer?

532
00:53:21,840 --> 00:53:25,040
Ready... Took it.

533
00:53:58,880 --> 00:54:00,280
One more.

534
00:54:01,520 --> 00:54:02,960
Now look at each other.

535
00:54:06,840 --> 00:54:09,240
If it’s about Mercan… I’ll risk everything.

536
00:54:09,960 --> 00:54:11,480
Even my life.

537
00:54:14,360 --> 00:54:16,480
If you love her that much,

538
00:54:17,680 --> 00:54:20,400
I’ll help you get her.

539
00:54:21,040 --> 00:54:23,680
Ateş won’t even look at her again.

540
00:54:42,680 --> 00:54:44,520
We're here!

541
00:55:05,520 --> 00:55:06,560
Give it to me.

542
00:55:28,160 --> 00:55:29,440
Uncle Durmuş?

543
00:55:42,200 --> 00:55:43,720
Uncle Durmuş?

544
00:55:56,040 --> 00:55:58,400
"Call me when you get back Ateş, son."

545
00:56:01,880 --> 00:56:03,000
That's weird.

546
00:56:06,600 --> 00:56:07,880
It is weird.

547
00:56:08,560 --> 00:56:09,840
I wonder what happened.

548
00:56:14,400 --> 00:56:16,520
Hello, Uncle Durmuş? Where are you?

549
00:56:16,560 --> 00:56:21,440
We went out for a good deed, son. The son of a close friend is getting engaged

550
00:56:21,440 --> 00:56:23,320
and we're accompanying him.

551
00:56:23,360 --> 00:56:25,880
We forgot to tell you, that's old age for you.

552
00:56:25,920 --> 00:56:27,200
We'll be back tomorrow.

553
00:56:27,200 --> 00:56:30,480
Don't you dare disappear, I'll be really upset.

554
00:56:31,120 --> 00:56:32,920
We'd love to have you over for longer.

555
00:56:34,280 --> 00:56:35,920
But without you at home...

556
00:56:35,960 --> 00:56:39,680
We leave our humble abode in your care, you're the master and mistress

557
00:56:39,720 --> 00:56:43,040
of the house while we're gone. Okay? See you later, take care!

558
00:56:43,800 --> 00:56:45,040
He hung up.

559
00:56:47,280 --> 00:56:49,160
What will we do now?

560
00:56:50,280 --> 00:56:52,200
I mean, they told us to stay but...

561
00:56:52,600 --> 00:56:55,440
Is it appropriate to stay here when they're not home?

562
00:56:56,320 --> 00:56:58,040
Should we go back home?

563
00:56:59,960 --> 00:57:01,760
I'm not sure either.

564
00:57:02,080 --> 00:57:04,200
He left the house in our care, too.

565
00:57:08,560 --> 00:57:11,680
It'd be rude to leave it unattended.

566
00:57:14,960 --> 00:57:16,640
What should we do?

567
00:57:17,360 --> 00:57:18,720
Let's have a seat, then.

568
00:57:19,960 --> 00:57:21,360
Good idea.

569
00:57:32,880 --> 00:57:36,000
You have the photos, right?

570
00:57:36,720 --> 00:57:37,880
Yes, I do.

571
00:57:37,920 --> 00:57:40,480
I couldn't get a good look at them, let me see.

572
00:57:57,840 --> 00:57:59,240
What's up with my face?

573
00:57:59,280 --> 00:58:02,040
I look awful, you need to destroy this one.

574
00:58:08,080 --> 00:58:09,200
No.

575
00:58:12,720 --> 00:58:14,240
You look beautiful.

576
00:58:21,480 --> 00:58:25,000
I mean, you look pretty good in the photo.

577
00:58:32,000 --> 00:58:35,040
This one turned out well, I like this one.

578
00:58:45,920 --> 00:58:47,160
I do, too.

579
00:58:54,280 --> 00:58:56,240
The photographer did a good job.

580
00:59:20,920 --> 00:59:22,400
Yes, mom?

581
00:59:22,440 --> 00:59:25,360
Hello, Ateş? Where are you, son?

582
00:59:25,400 --> 00:59:27,360
I couldn't find you home, I got worried.

583
00:59:27,360 --> 00:59:30,240
We're fine, mom. We're at uncle Durmuş'.

584
00:59:30,960 --> 00:59:33,600
Is that so? Will you be back for dinner,

585
00:59:33,640 --> 00:59:35,880
should we put plates out for you?

586
00:59:35,920 --> 00:59:38,520
We'll stay here tonight, don't wait up.

587
00:59:39,640 --> 00:59:42,600
Okay, say hi to Mr. Durmuş for me.

588
00:59:42,600 --> 00:59:46,760
They had some business to attend to, I'll tell them when they get back.

589
00:59:48,080 --> 00:59:49,320
Take care.

590
01:00:01,600 --> 01:00:03,480
Are they staying the night?

591
01:00:05,560 --> 01:00:06,520
Yes.

592
01:00:10,240 --> 01:00:11,800
I can't stand it anymore.

593
01:00:15,880 --> 01:00:17,240
And it's just the two of them.

594
01:00:19,560 --> 01:00:23,280
Tomorrow will be a day no one will be able to forget.

595
01:00:23,280 --> 01:00:25,560
Especially Ateş.

596
01:00:26,280 --> 01:00:30,800
Let's see if he can still call her his wife after finding out her betrayal.

597
01:00:32,640 --> 01:00:34,080
We'll see.

598
01:00:46,760 --> 01:00:49,680
We'll greet the patients like this, okay?

599
01:00:50,240 --> 01:00:53,560
You make a note of that and then, let me know.

600
01:00:57,120 --> 01:01:00,760
What's up? Why did Mr. Nezir stare at you like that?

601
01:01:00,800 --> 01:01:02,680
Is there something wrong?

602
01:01:04,360 --> 01:01:06,240
He wasn't staring at me, you must've seen wrong.

603
01:01:06,960 --> 01:01:08,200
I saw wrong?

604
01:01:08,240 --> 01:01:09,160
Uh-huh.

605
01:01:12,880 --> 01:01:14,000
Ms. Zahide?

606
01:01:15,800 --> 01:01:16,960
Have you been crying?

607
01:01:16,960 --> 01:01:19,520
No, I haven't. Why would I be?

608
01:01:21,280 --> 01:01:23,920
Why is everyone treating me like I can't see properly today?

609
01:01:23,920 --> 01:01:25,320
What are you talking about?

610
01:01:25,320 --> 01:01:26,960
Nothing.

611
01:01:29,280 --> 01:01:33,480
I mean...If you wanted to talk to someone, or a shoulder to cry on, I'm here for you.

612
01:01:36,560 --> 01:01:40,520
I saw a cat on my way here, I had to take her to the vet...

613
01:01:41,640 --> 01:01:43,160
Poor thing.

614
01:01:43,200 --> 01:01:46,720
I feel awful. So, that's why you're sad.

615
01:01:48,520 --> 01:01:53,080
The vet said she's in a criticial conditon but that he'd do everything in his power.

616
01:01:53,080 --> 01:01:56,880
Don't worry, cats are resilient animals. She'll get better, she'll pull through.

617
01:01:56,920 --> 01:01:58,160
Don't you worry.

618
01:01:58,200 --> 01:02:00,640
I hope so. I hope you're right.

619
01:02:02,080 --> 01:02:03,840
So, you're a cat person, too?

620
01:02:03,840 --> 01:02:06,280
I mean, like me. I'm a cat person too.

621
01:02:06,320 --> 01:02:07,760
I'm delighted.

622
01:02:07,800 --> 01:02:12,320
I have two cats, orange tabbies. They wait for me at home like Azrael.

623
01:02:13,520 --> 01:02:16,000
So you're a cat person? That's a surprise.

624
01:02:16,040 --> 01:02:18,480
I'm surprised too, I didn't expect you to be a cat person.

625
01:02:20,400 --> 01:02:22,680
So, Zahides have hearts as well.

626
01:02:24,520 --> 01:02:26,840
Why did I even bother talking to you?

627
01:02:26,880 --> 01:02:29,880
Wait a minute, wait! It's not like I said something wrong.

628
01:02:31,600 --> 01:02:34,120
What's up with her? Did I say something wrong?

629
01:02:35,080 --> 01:02:37,000
What happened? I didn't catch it.

630
01:02:39,400 --> 01:02:41,720
Did I say something to upset her, what was that about?

631
01:02:41,720 --> 01:02:44,640
Forget about it, Yaşar. Don't try in vain to understand women.

632
01:02:45,360 --> 01:02:47,680
Why are you acting like an wxpert on women?

633
01:02:47,680 --> 01:02:52,960
I'm reading a book to understand women, it's called "Understanding Women".

634
01:02:53,000 --> 01:02:56,520
Keep reading, read it well. You'll get it soon, keep reading.

635
01:03:16,880 --> 01:03:18,560
Should we make a salad?

636
01:03:20,920 --> 01:03:22,000
Salad?

637
01:03:22,400 --> 01:03:24,720
We bought all these ingredients to cook something.

638
01:03:25,320 --> 01:03:30,280
But I... I don't know how to cook.

639
01:03:32,520 --> 01:03:34,840
I thought you were avoiding the work.

640
01:03:34,840 --> 01:03:36,080
Really?

641
01:03:36,440 --> 01:03:37,840
Really.

642
01:03:37,880 --> 01:03:42,120
I can bake a little but as much as Ms. Güllü has taught me.

643
01:03:42,800 --> 01:03:46,160
So, you know to beat up men, but not how to cook, is that so?

644
01:03:46,200 --> 01:03:49,720
Those two are not up for comparison, they're completely different.

645
01:03:50,480 --> 01:03:51,840
Let's make a deal.

646
01:03:51,880 --> 01:03:55,120
Fighting is my job and cooking is yours.

647
01:03:55,160 --> 01:03:56,120
Do you hear me?

648
01:03:56,160 --> 01:03:59,120
You're the lady of the house, you'll cook the meals.

649
01:03:59,160 --> 01:04:00,480
Is that so?

650
01:04:00,480 --> 01:04:04,440
Why would I, is there a law that says I have to cook?

651
01:04:05,400 --> 01:04:08,000
We're equals in this house.

652
01:04:08,000 --> 01:04:13,160
If you know how to, you'll cook and I'll assist you.

653
01:04:16,040 --> 01:04:17,440
Spoiled princess.

654
01:04:17,480 --> 01:04:19,320
You don't feel like learning, do you?

655
01:04:19,360 --> 01:04:20,560
Of course I don't.

656
01:04:20,560 --> 01:04:23,640
If I learn, you'll always expect me to cook.

657
01:04:24,680 --> 01:04:25,840
Yes, I would.

658
01:04:26,400 --> 01:04:29,120
Come on, hurry up. I'm starving.

659
01:04:29,160 --> 01:04:33,160
I trust you, I think you'll be a great cook.

660
01:04:35,240 --> 01:04:36,560
Okay, I'll give it a go.

661
01:04:37,040 --> 01:04:39,880
But let's make a deal first. You won't make fun of me.

662
01:04:40,560 --> 01:04:41,600
I won't.

663
01:04:41,640 --> 01:04:45,040
Okay, then. What are we making?

664
01:04:45,920 --> 01:04:47,360
Let's start with something simple.

665
01:04:51,720 --> 01:04:54,080
Lentil soup is always a good one. Here you go.

666
01:04:56,200 --> 01:04:59,440
Okay, then you give me directions. Where do I begin?

667
01:05:00,320 --> 01:05:01,720
Chop the onions.

668
01:05:14,320 --> 01:05:15,400
Knife...

669
01:05:22,080 --> 01:05:23,200
Wait, hold up!

670
01:05:24,320 --> 01:05:25,400
What are you doing?

671
01:05:25,840 --> 01:05:27,720
I'm peeling the onion.

672
01:05:28,720 --> 01:05:30,400
You're wasting the onion.

673
01:05:30,440 --> 01:05:32,880
You cut off half of it with its peel.

674
01:05:32,920 --> 01:05:35,000
That's not how you peel, this is how you do it.

675
01:05:50,080 --> 01:05:52,160
You hold it like this and pull.

676
01:05:53,560 --> 01:05:54,560
See?

677
01:05:55,320 --> 01:05:57,200
Okay, I get it.

678
01:06:17,680 --> 01:06:19,000
Don't cry.

679
01:06:19,240 --> 01:06:21,320
I don't know what happened.

680
01:06:23,520 --> 01:06:24,800
Did you get sentimental?

681
01:06:25,840 --> 01:06:27,720
You said you wouldn't make fun.

682
01:06:28,200 --> 01:06:29,160
I'm not.

683
01:06:29,200 --> 01:06:30,400
You are!

684
01:06:39,160 --> 01:06:41,360
Wait, stop. Those pieces are way too big.

685
01:06:43,280 --> 01:06:46,480
I wish you'd stop talking and help out with something else.

686
01:06:46,520 --> 01:06:50,120
You're the cook. Hurry up, I'm going to starve to death.

687
01:06:53,240 --> 01:06:54,840
Let me show you.

688
01:06:55,800 --> 01:06:58,720
Watch me. I'll show you how to do it.

689
01:07:00,000 --> 01:07:01,600
This is how it's done.

690
01:07:02,160 --> 01:07:05,880
You only move your wrist, watch carefully.

691
01:07:20,560 --> 01:07:21,600
See?

692
01:07:35,200 --> 01:07:36,280
I need to...

693
01:07:37,520 --> 01:07:40,640
I'll help with something else. What should I do?

694
01:07:40,640 --> 01:07:42,000
You should get a pot.

695
01:07:42,000 --> 01:07:43,520
I'll get a pot.

696
01:08:14,520 --> 01:08:15,960
What are you doing?

697
01:08:20,360 --> 01:08:22,800
I'm leaving you to your own devices right now, because

698
01:08:22,840 --> 01:08:25,000
I don't want to kill you over some lentil soup.

699
01:08:25,000 --> 01:08:26,920
I'm putting the oil in, what else?

700
01:08:28,560 --> 01:08:29,880
Stop exaggerating.

701
01:08:31,520 --> 01:08:33,840
You never know, I have to watch my back.

702
01:08:36,520 --> 01:08:39,640
Yes, you should watch your back. That's too much oil.

703
01:08:40,480 --> 01:08:42,920
The flavor is in the oil, the food would be bland without it.

704
01:08:43,720 --> 01:08:45,640
And too much oil makes you fat.

705
01:08:47,360 --> 01:08:50,400
It would do you some good, you're too thin.

706
01:08:52,840 --> 01:08:54,160
You look like Olive Oyl.

707
01:08:55,400 --> 01:08:58,800
Olive Oyl had two men in love with him, mind you.

708
01:08:58,840 --> 01:09:00,400
Am I really that thin?

709
01:09:01,440 --> 01:09:02,560
You are.

710
01:09:03,080 --> 01:09:07,560
And you know what they say, some meat on the bones covers flaws.

711
01:09:08,360 --> 01:09:13,080
They also say to eat to live, not live to eat.

712
01:09:13,120 --> 01:09:16,440
They also say you can have too much of a good thing.

713
01:09:17,160 --> 01:09:19,160
That's okay with me, we have a deal.

714
01:09:19,200 --> 01:09:20,680
Fine by me, too. It's a deal.

715
01:09:21,840 --> 01:09:24,840
If we have a deal on this topic, let's move on to the next one.

716
01:09:25,280 --> 01:09:26,320
Listen carefully.

717
01:09:29,240 --> 01:09:30,680
Where are the potatoes?

718
01:09:31,840 --> 01:09:32,920
Here they are.

719
01:09:34,560 --> 01:09:35,800
Here you go.

720
01:09:35,800 --> 01:09:38,600
You need to peel and chop the potato and the carrot.

721
01:09:38,600 --> 01:09:40,720
Then, you'll put them all into the pot.

722
01:09:40,720 --> 01:09:45,200
Then, we'll put the lentils and the spices in but no red pepper flakes.

723
01:09:45,800 --> 01:09:46,920
Why not?

724
01:09:47,680 --> 01:09:49,400
Because you don't like spicy food.

725
01:09:49,920 --> 01:09:51,800
In the contrary, I love spicy food.

726
01:09:52,280 --> 01:09:53,320
Is that so?

727
01:09:53,920 --> 01:09:56,240
I'm glad we see eye to eye on this.

728
01:09:57,880 --> 01:10:01,400
Yeah? I could tell you feed on pain.

729
01:10:02,760 --> 01:10:03,920
Know-it-all.

730
01:10:34,440 --> 01:10:37,880
While you're leisurely sipping your coffee over here,

731
01:10:38,200 --> 01:10:40,600
do you know where Ateş and Mercan are?

732
01:10:41,800 --> 01:10:42,880
Where are they?

733
01:10:43,680 --> 01:10:45,720
They're at Durmuş' house in the village again.

734
01:10:45,760 --> 01:10:47,320
Just the two of them.

735
01:10:48,200 --> 01:10:49,280
So?

736
01:10:50,040 --> 01:10:53,320
If I were you, I'd go and spoil their fun.

737
01:10:54,480 --> 01:10:56,000
You're not well, you know.

738
01:10:56,680 --> 01:10:58,880
You can't think clearly.

739
01:10:59,720 --> 01:11:01,680
I talked to your mom, we'll figure something out.

740
01:11:02,280 --> 01:11:04,440
I'm telling you they're staying the night there.

741
01:11:04,480 --> 01:11:05,800
Just the two of them.

742
01:11:05,800 --> 01:11:08,080
Why is no one listening to me?

743
01:11:08,080 --> 01:11:10,960
Could it be because you're being ridiculous?

744
01:11:12,640 --> 01:11:14,720
Don't you dare try to hurt Mercan,

745
01:11:15,640 --> 01:11:17,200
or I'll kill you.

746
01:11:17,840 --> 01:11:20,240
How can you put up with this?

747
01:11:23,120 --> 01:11:24,240
Listen.

748
01:11:25,080 --> 01:11:27,520
I'm blindly in love with Mercan,

749
01:11:29,000 --> 01:11:32,080
do you hear me? I always get what I want in life.

750
01:11:32,520 --> 01:11:33,600
She'll be no exception.

751
01:11:33,600 --> 01:11:36,120
When it's time, I'll have her, as well.

752
01:11:36,600 --> 01:11:38,560
That's why I'm biding my time for now.

753
01:11:39,400 --> 01:11:41,280
I recommend you do the same.

754
01:11:41,920 --> 01:11:46,320
Because these silly moves you keep making, only bring them closer together.

755
01:11:47,360 --> 01:11:50,400
You're in no position to give me any advice.

756
01:11:51,720 --> 01:11:52,920
Okay.

757
01:11:53,320 --> 01:11:57,560
If you don't want to listen to me, listen to your mother.

758
01:11:57,560 --> 01:11:59,920
She has a plan, don't ruin it.

759
01:12:00,840 --> 01:12:01,880
Okay?

760
01:12:01,880 --> 01:12:05,680
Now go back to your house and stay away from Mercan until tomorrow.

761
01:12:05,680 --> 01:12:08,280
Stay away from her forever while you're at it.

762
01:12:17,640 --> 01:12:19,160
She's crazy.

763
01:13:35,320 --> 01:13:36,840
Did you burn yourself? Let me.

764
01:13:50,320 --> 01:13:51,080
Well...

765
01:13:51,120 --> 01:13:54,600
Do you think the soup is done?

766
01:13:55,920 --> 01:13:57,000
It's done.

767
01:13:57,600 --> 01:14:00,120
But now we need to run it through a blender.

768
01:14:01,360 --> 01:14:03,640
Blender? Where is the blender?

769
01:14:03,680 --> 01:14:05,800
Check that cabinet, maybe it's in there.

770
01:14:21,760 --> 01:14:23,760
There's no blender, what do we do now?

771
01:14:23,760 --> 01:14:25,680
It's okay, we can eat it like this.

772
01:14:27,000 --> 01:14:28,480
Wait, hold on a second.

773
01:14:28,520 --> 01:14:32,160
Let me call Binnaz and ask her, she'll know how to do it.

774
01:14:37,240 --> 01:14:38,760
Binnaz, how are you doing?

775
01:14:38,760 --> 01:14:41,720
I have a question for you if you're free to talk.

776
01:14:42,280 --> 01:14:44,760
We just made red lentil soup...

777
01:14:46,680 --> 01:14:50,280
There's no blender at home, do you know how else we can blend it?

778
01:14:54,160 --> 01:14:57,280
With what? We should strain it?

779
01:15:00,520 --> 01:15:01,560
How do you mean?

780
01:15:01,560 --> 01:15:04,600
I need to strain it through a fine strainer?

781
01:15:06,080 --> 01:15:08,760
Okay, if you say so.

782
01:15:08,800 --> 01:15:10,400
Thank you, Binnaz.

783
01:15:12,360 --> 01:15:13,440
What did she say?

784
01:15:14,760 --> 01:15:16,760
She says to run it through a wire mesh strainer.

785
01:15:16,760 --> 01:15:18,480
I don't really get it.

786
01:15:21,200 --> 01:15:23,000
That's how they used to do it.

787
01:15:24,760 --> 01:15:26,680
Like you know so well.

788
01:15:27,440 --> 01:15:28,680
I do know.

789
01:15:29,640 --> 01:15:32,320
Why didn't you tell me before I called if you knew?

790
01:15:32,920 --> 01:15:34,880
You should hone your investigative skills,

791
01:15:34,920 --> 01:15:36,680
I can't just give you all the answers.

792
01:15:39,440 --> 01:15:41,080
Let's strain it, then. Come on.

793
01:15:46,600 --> 01:15:48,480
Could you give me another pot?

794
01:15:50,000 --> 01:15:51,080
It might be at the bottom.

795
01:15:52,680 --> 01:15:53,680
This one.

796
01:15:54,640 --> 01:15:55,800
Would this one work?

797
01:15:55,840 --> 01:15:56,800
It would.

798
01:15:56,840 --> 01:15:58,160
Give me.

799
01:16:16,600 --> 01:16:18,720
Like this? Am I doing it correctly?

800
01:16:18,760 --> 01:16:20,920
Yes. You are.

801
01:16:20,920 --> 01:16:22,440
Good.

802
01:16:33,000 --> 01:16:33,960
Did you burn yourself?

803
01:16:34,880 --> 01:16:36,560
It's okay, don't worry about it.

804
01:16:36,600 --> 01:16:38,200
Just give me your hand, don't argue.

805
01:16:54,960 --> 01:16:56,400
That's enough, I'm fine now.

806
01:16:56,440 --> 01:16:57,960
Wait, let me check.

807
01:17:14,200 --> 01:17:16,680
I'm fine, I'm okay. It doesn't hurt anymore.

808
01:17:20,160 --> 01:17:21,640
Let's taste the soup.

809
01:17:30,720 --> 01:17:33,320
Yum. It's really good.

810
01:17:35,800 --> 01:17:37,280
Taste it.

811
01:17:43,080 --> 01:17:44,960
Binnaz said to melt some butter

812
01:17:45,000 --> 01:17:47,720
and pour it over after straining the soup.

813
01:17:49,040 --> 01:17:50,520
It's done after we do that.

814
01:17:50,840 --> 01:17:51,880
Okay.

815
01:17:57,280 --> 01:17:59,640
Come on, we should get it done already.

816
01:18:21,360 --> 01:18:25,320
Mercan sounded really well over the phone.

817
01:18:26,040 --> 01:18:28,280
May god protect our children.

818
01:18:36,560 --> 01:18:39,440
You have your head in the clouds now, so you must not care.

819
01:18:41,680 --> 01:18:43,520
You always want to see him.

820
01:18:44,800 --> 01:18:49,920
You think everything will be perfect as long as he's beside you.

821
01:18:53,240 --> 01:18:54,320
Çiçek, dear.

822
01:18:54,840 --> 01:18:56,800
I've been young too.

823
01:19:01,160 --> 01:19:04,640
I fell for your father's green eyes the moment I saw him.

824
01:19:05,520 --> 01:19:08,200
I didn't want to hear my mom and dad, I wanted to be with him.

825
01:19:09,120 --> 01:19:10,880
I ran away with him.

826
01:19:12,840 --> 01:19:15,440
But love goes out as fast as it burns.

827
01:19:15,480 --> 01:19:16,920
It burned out really fast.

828
01:19:20,440 --> 01:19:22,680
Then reality kicked in.

829
01:19:25,880 --> 01:19:27,440
Look at these hands, Çiçek.

830
01:19:27,440 --> 01:19:30,200
I picked tea leaves with these hands on fields and hills.

831
01:19:32,400 --> 01:19:34,400
I made a home.

832
01:19:34,440 --> 01:19:37,040
I raised two children, Çiçek.

833
01:19:39,800 --> 01:19:41,280
But what does it matter?

834
01:19:41,280 --> 01:19:42,800
What good has it done?

835
01:19:47,160 --> 01:19:49,160
I suffered a lot.

836
01:19:51,560 --> 01:19:53,480
Away from my home...

837
01:19:54,960 --> 01:20:00,040
No mom or dad to listen to me, watch over me.

838
01:20:07,680 --> 01:20:11,000
That path you want to go down on?

839
01:20:13,000 --> 01:20:16,480
I've already walked through that path.

840
01:20:18,280 --> 01:20:20,680
And then, I made a promise to myself,

841
01:20:20,680 --> 01:20:26,400
I swore my children would be like me, they wouldn't suffer like alone I have.

842
01:20:27,520 --> 01:20:32,640
I swore that I'd keep them safe, that I'd keep them under my wings, Çiçek.

843
01:20:36,760 --> 01:20:39,240
But look at where I found myself, look where I ended up.

844
01:20:39,760 --> 01:20:43,440
Life has forced me to live my worst nightmare.

845
01:22:00,320 --> 01:22:02,120
I wonder how the soup turned out.

846
01:22:02,120 --> 01:22:03,520
We'll see now.

847
01:22:06,640 --> 01:22:07,960
Give it a taste.

848
01:22:11,120 --> 01:22:12,320
You burned me.

849
01:22:13,840 --> 01:22:15,040
That's weird.

850
01:22:15,040 --> 01:22:18,600
You're called "fire", aren't you usually the one who burns?

851
01:22:30,240 --> 01:22:31,800
How does it taste, is it good?

852
01:22:31,800 --> 01:22:33,640
It's okay.

853
01:22:33,640 --> 01:22:35,440
Just okay?

854
01:22:35,440 --> 01:22:37,320
What do you want me to say? It's okay.

855
01:22:37,320 --> 01:22:39,960
I put in a lot of effort, is that all you have to say?

856
01:22:41,000 --> 01:22:42,920
Okay, I'm sorry. Don't get mad, come here.

857
01:22:44,240 --> 01:22:45,520
It's delicious.

858
01:22:46,440 --> 01:22:48,120
You're only saying that to appease me.

859
01:22:48,160 --> 01:22:49,520
I'm not.

860
01:22:50,440 --> 01:22:51,920
It's good.

861
01:22:55,760 --> 01:22:57,440
It's really good.

862
01:23:08,120 --> 01:23:09,960
And it smells good too.

863
01:23:17,720 --> 01:23:19,440
I'm glad you like it.

864
01:23:19,480 --> 01:23:21,920
I'll go set the table then.

865
01:23:22,680 --> 01:23:24,360
Let me help you with the plates.

866
01:23:24,400 --> 01:23:26,720
No, you go sit.

867
01:23:27,320 --> 01:23:28,880
I'm the lady of the house, you know.

868
01:23:28,880 --> 01:23:30,400
I'll set the table.

869
01:23:30,720 --> 01:23:32,040
Honey.

870
01:23:42,760 --> 01:23:44,240
Honey?

871
01:23:46,880 --> 01:23:48,320
She called me honey.

872
01:23:50,680 --> 01:23:51,920
Okay,

873
01:23:53,360 --> 01:23:54,520
honey.

874
01:23:59,680 --> 01:24:02,040
Why do you keep looking around?

875
01:24:03,720 --> 01:24:07,680
I'm checking to see if mom's around, if she sees us I'll get an earful.

876
01:24:07,720 --> 01:24:10,040
Maybe we shouldn't see each other at all then,

877
01:24:10,040 --> 01:24:12,160
so your mom never has to see us together.

878
01:24:12,200 --> 01:24:14,080
Calm down, lower your voice.

879
01:24:14,120 --> 01:24:17,760
What if someone hears, this is not my private estate.

880
01:24:17,800 --> 01:24:18,920
Fine.

881
01:24:18,920 --> 01:24:21,160
Zehra, come on.

882
01:24:24,440 --> 01:24:25,880
Don't be like this.

883
01:24:26,920 --> 01:24:28,600
I can't live without you.

884
01:24:29,240 --> 01:24:31,600
You never leave my mind for a second,

885
01:24:31,600 --> 01:24:33,000
day or night, Zehra.

886
01:24:33,040 --> 01:24:36,720
If that's the case, you should be brave like Malik.

887
01:24:36,720 --> 01:24:38,840
You know how he stepped up for his love.

888
01:24:38,840 --> 01:24:40,640
He put a finger on Çiçek's finger.

889
01:24:40,680 --> 01:24:44,840
Don't mention Malik. I lose my head when I hear his name.

890
01:24:47,680 --> 01:24:50,400
It was wrong of him to go behind your back, of course,

891
01:24:54,360 --> 01:24:56,880
but he had the guts to hold Çiçek's hand, didn't he?

892
01:24:56,920 --> 01:24:59,680
He made a promise and he kept it.

893
01:25:03,640 --> 01:25:05,360
Mom is coming, I have to go.

894
01:25:09,800 --> 01:25:10,840
Keep still.

895
01:25:14,200 --> 01:25:16,160
How can a man fear his mother so much?

896
01:25:16,200 --> 01:25:17,720
What a man you are, Berat.

897
01:25:49,920 --> 01:25:51,960
Okay, here's the soup.

898
01:25:52,600 --> 01:25:54,400
Come on, have a seat. The table's ready.

899
01:26:03,480 --> 01:26:04,760
Thank you.

900
01:26:04,800 --> 01:26:06,720
Everything looks delicious.

901
01:26:06,720 --> 01:26:07,760
Enjoy.

902
01:26:33,080 --> 01:26:34,480
Enjoy.

903
01:26:34,480 --> 01:26:35,640
You too.

904
01:26:36,240 --> 01:26:39,680
May god bless our food.

905
01:26:45,120 --> 01:26:46,160
It's good.

906
01:26:48,200 --> 01:26:49,960
Thank you for the food, it's really good.

907
01:26:50,000 --> 01:26:52,320
I should be thanking you.

908
01:27:05,000 --> 01:27:08,240
See this? This is the best part of the onion.

909
01:27:16,440 --> 01:27:17,480
How is it?

910
01:27:17,520 --> 01:27:18,640
It's really good.

911
01:27:19,120 --> 01:27:20,200
Do you like it?

912
01:27:20,560 --> 01:27:21,640
I love it.

913
01:27:27,040 --> 01:27:28,720
This place has been really good for me.

914
01:27:28,720 --> 01:27:30,640
It made me forget my problems.

915
01:27:33,320 --> 01:27:34,520
I'm happy to hear that.

916
01:27:36,040 --> 01:27:38,000
But I really miss working, I'll get

917
01:27:38,000 --> 01:27:40,040
back to work the moment we get back.

918
01:27:41,480 --> 01:27:44,960
You're not in any hurry, you can stay and rest for a while more.

919
01:27:45,000 --> 01:27:46,960
Everything's in line at the company.

920
01:27:47,840 --> 01:27:49,920
So, I'm not needed there, is that so?

921
01:27:51,080 --> 01:27:52,640
Everything's going well.

922
01:27:54,280 --> 01:27:56,720
I know you're saying that to upset me.

923
01:28:00,440 --> 01:28:03,200
That's a first. You didn't fall for it this time.

924
01:28:05,560 --> 01:28:10,160
The hospital project got delayed due to what happened.

925
01:28:12,280 --> 01:28:15,320
When we get back, I'll get things in rapid motion.

926
01:28:15,760 --> 01:28:19,360
I'm thinking about finishing it in a year if all goes well.

927
01:28:19,360 --> 01:28:22,240
I'm planning a big opening.

928
01:28:22,280 --> 01:28:26,880
You know the conference hall that's next to the company building?

929
01:28:26,920 --> 01:28:28,600
I'm planning on having it there.

930
01:28:28,600 --> 01:28:32,360
I also have a friend who's an event planner and he's a really good one,

931
01:28:32,400 --> 01:28:35,680
I'd talked to him about it, planned everything beforehand...

932
01:28:46,960 --> 01:28:48,360
You're not listening to me!

933
01:28:49,440 --> 01:28:51,160
What? I am listening.

934
01:28:51,200 --> 01:28:53,080
I'm listening, why wouldn't I?

935
01:28:53,080 --> 01:28:54,720
What was I saying, then?

936
01:28:55,760 --> 01:28:57,920
You talked about the hospital, and

937
01:28:57,960 --> 01:29:00,640
its opening, said something about a show, I think.

938
01:29:00,680 --> 01:29:01,720
You think?

939
01:29:02,640 --> 01:29:04,160
See? You weren't listening.

940
01:29:06,360 --> 01:29:08,240
I'm sorry, I must've zoned out.

941
01:29:09,160 --> 01:29:10,360
It's okay.

942
01:29:19,720 --> 01:29:22,000
The soup turned out really good.

943
01:29:22,000 --> 01:29:25,920
Some tea after this would be the cherry on top.

944
01:29:27,440 --> 01:29:29,360
I already made the tea.

945
01:29:29,400 --> 01:29:30,400
When?

946
01:29:31,680 --> 01:29:34,160
I took care of so many things while you were sitting around.

947
01:29:40,560 --> 01:29:42,760
Enough with the salad, have some bread.

948
01:29:42,760 --> 01:29:44,560
You're all skin and bones.

949
01:29:46,120 --> 01:29:47,520
Here, let me.

950
01:29:50,640 --> 01:29:51,880
Open your mouth.

951
01:29:59,840 --> 01:30:01,440
Soup should be enjoyed with bread.

952
01:30:02,720 --> 01:30:04,040
You can't just drink it.

953
01:30:04,040 --> 01:30:05,400
That's why you're so thin.

954
01:30:06,760 --> 01:30:08,040
I'm not thin.

955
01:30:53,640 --> 01:30:56,400
You don't deserve anything good.

956
01:31:00,120 --> 01:31:02,680
I would love to destroy this room all over again.

957
01:31:04,080 --> 01:31:05,840
I'll save it for later.

958
01:31:42,560 --> 01:31:45,520
I won't let you take what's mine.

959
01:31:49,560 --> 01:31:51,440
I'll get rid of you.

960
01:32:05,920 --> 01:32:07,240
Mom.

961
01:32:08,640 --> 01:32:09,880
It was you.

962
01:32:12,320 --> 01:32:14,520
Did you do what I told you to?

963
01:32:22,120 --> 01:32:24,200
Okay, good. Let's leave before someone comes in.

964
01:32:56,760 --> 01:32:58,920
At least you know how to make tea.

965
01:32:59,720 --> 01:33:01,800
I might be getting ahead of myself, though.

966
01:33:03,760 --> 01:33:06,840
We'll see if you do or don't know how to make tea.

967
01:33:06,840 --> 01:33:10,000
Make fun all you want, I don't care.

968
01:33:10,040 --> 01:33:11,800
Is that so?

969
01:33:11,800 --> 01:33:15,200
Okay but you have to promise not to get upset if I do.

970
01:33:15,240 --> 01:33:18,520
I don't know, I can't make that promise.

971
01:33:19,240 --> 01:33:20,720
You must care, then.

972
01:33:26,280 --> 01:33:28,000
Good. It's excellent.

973
01:33:29,600 --> 01:33:31,640
I assume you like it, then.

974
01:33:35,080 --> 01:33:36,160
It's great.

975
01:33:37,360 --> 01:33:38,440
Thank you.

976
01:33:38,480 --> 01:33:40,360
It's the best after having a meal.

977
01:33:40,960 --> 01:33:43,640
I tried to make it how you like it.

978
01:33:45,960 --> 01:33:47,680
You know how I like my tea?

979
01:33:56,120 --> 01:34:00,000
This place is so tranquil and serene, don't you think?

980
01:34:02,160 --> 01:34:03,440
It is.

981
01:34:03,440 --> 01:34:04,960
It's really peaceful.

982
01:34:06,480 --> 01:34:08,040
Away from all the chaos.

983
01:34:11,080 --> 01:34:12,280
Feels really far away.

984
01:34:14,120 --> 01:34:15,960
I feel wonderful here.

985
01:34:16,640 --> 01:34:21,520
It's as though I've always belonged here, in this moment.

986
01:34:22,440 --> 01:34:24,760
It's strange, I can't really describe it.

987
01:34:25,360 --> 01:34:26,960
Do you feel that way too?

988
01:34:28,680 --> 01:34:30,560
As if we'll stay in this moment forever.

989
01:34:53,240 --> 01:34:54,600
Let me get this.

990
01:35:00,720 --> 01:35:02,160
How are you, Cemal?

991
01:35:02,680 --> 01:35:05,240
I'm good, brother. How are you two doing?

992
01:35:05,280 --> 01:35:06,720
Nothing out of the ordinary.

993
01:35:06,720 --> 01:35:08,280
That's good. How's Mercan?

994
01:35:11,240 --> 01:35:13,360
She's doing better. Much better, actually.

995
01:35:14,000 --> 01:35:15,280
You sound good, too.

996
01:35:15,280 --> 01:35:18,800
Beyond good, you sound joyful. That place did you good, I suppose.

997
01:35:19,720 --> 01:35:21,320
Has the police said anything?

998
01:35:21,920 --> 01:35:22,680
Yes.

999
01:35:22,720 --> 01:35:24,920
There are inital findings pointing to a suicide.

1000
01:35:25,320 --> 01:35:29,240
He has a long rap sheet. Bodily harm, battery, violence.

1001
01:35:29,280 --> 01:35:30,320
You name it.

1002
01:35:31,640 --> 01:35:35,120
It would've been better if we'd got there earlier, got him to talk.

1003
01:35:35,160 --> 01:35:37,520
What is it? Do you still have doubts?

1004
01:35:37,560 --> 01:35:40,240
Like I said, some things don't make sense to me.

1005
01:35:40,240 --> 01:35:41,200
It doesn't fit.

1006
01:35:42,120 --> 01:35:44,760
This guy attempting something like this

1007
01:35:44,800 --> 01:35:47,200
is a puzzle piece that doesn't fit.

1008
01:35:48,200 --> 01:35:50,320
The police is looking for people who saw him last.

1009
01:35:50,320 --> 01:35:53,760
They're probably checking to see if there's anyone else behind it.

1010
01:35:53,760 --> 01:35:55,440
That's all the information we have.

1011
01:35:55,440 --> 01:35:57,400
Okay, Cemal. Thank you.

1012
01:36:12,520 --> 01:36:14,000
You have to win.

1013
01:36:16,040 --> 01:36:18,200
You can't let her beat you.

1014
01:36:28,000 --> 01:36:29,200
Who are you talking to?

1015
01:36:32,400 --> 01:36:35,520
From the outside, it looked like a deep conversation.

1016
01:36:37,200 --> 01:36:38,160
It was.

1017
01:36:38,200 --> 01:36:39,760
Won't you tell me about it?

1018
01:36:43,320 --> 01:36:45,640
It's like there's a person on earth,

1019
01:36:47,240 --> 01:36:50,240
who shows me what I lost every time I look at her.

1020
01:36:54,360 --> 01:36:56,440
It feels like, in the whole world,

1021
01:36:57,600 --> 01:37:00,480
there's only him and I and

1022
01:37:00,480 --> 01:37:04,920
that shadow that's come in-between us.

1023
01:37:08,120 --> 01:37:11,040
I can't get over that shadow no matter what I do.

1024
01:37:20,000 --> 01:37:21,960
Have you talked to Ateş?

1025
01:37:24,080 --> 01:37:26,440
Of course you have.

1026
01:37:27,440 --> 01:37:29,240
Are they feeling alright, then?

1027
01:37:30,040 --> 01:37:32,160
Mercan must be doing well too.

1028
01:37:32,200 --> 01:37:34,240
She has her husband with her after all.

1029
01:37:36,880 --> 01:37:39,160
Let me give you some friendly advice, Aslı.

1030
01:37:40,640 --> 01:37:42,240
Stop doing this to yourself.

1031
01:37:45,280 --> 01:37:46,280
I will.

1032
01:37:47,920 --> 01:37:50,360
I just need some time.

1033
01:37:58,720 --> 01:38:00,080
I wish you'd see,

1034
01:38:01,880 --> 01:38:06,480
how my heart beats for you, how it burns for you.

1035
01:38:08,400 --> 01:38:09,920
I wish you'd understand my heart.

1036
01:38:11,640 --> 01:38:14,120
In this lonely world where no one understands me.

1037
01:38:15,040 --> 01:38:16,680
If only you could understand.

1038
01:38:18,640 --> 01:38:22,200
Although, I don't have the guts to tell you how I feel.

1039
01:38:23,280 --> 01:38:25,400
I'm scared of losing what I have of you.

1040
01:38:43,080 --> 01:38:44,400
Are you sleepy?

1041
01:38:45,040 --> 01:38:46,080
Not really.

1042
01:38:47,960 --> 01:38:50,280
But you obviously are.

1043
01:38:51,640 --> 01:38:52,720
No, I'm not.

1044
01:38:52,720 --> 01:38:54,280
You're the one yawning.

1045
01:38:57,200 --> 01:38:59,400
I'll sleep here, you sleep in the bed.

1046
01:38:59,440 --> 01:39:00,480
No.

1047
01:39:01,680 --> 01:39:05,000
I mean, I'll take the couch. You should sleep in the bed.

1048
01:39:05,040 --> 01:39:07,760
No, you sleep in the bed. I don't feel like sleeping anyway.

1049
01:39:08,840 --> 01:39:10,080
I don't, either.

1050
01:39:11,000 --> 01:39:12,320
You yawned.

1051
01:39:13,640 --> 01:39:14,880
I think I ate too much.

1052
01:39:14,880 --> 01:39:17,800
It must be because of all the bread you forced on me.

1053
01:39:20,200 --> 01:39:22,680
Then, should we watch a movie?

1054
01:39:25,200 --> 01:39:28,040
A movie would be nice, that's a good idea.

1055
01:39:29,000 --> 01:39:31,360
We haven't been able to watch a movie before.

1056
01:39:32,560 --> 01:39:34,560
You never miss an opportunity.

1057
01:39:34,560 --> 01:39:37,360
Well, am I wrong? You owe me a movie.

1058
01:39:37,360 --> 01:39:39,280
Okay, I'll pay my debt.

1059
01:39:39,320 --> 01:39:41,120
We're having a movie night.

1060
01:39:42,080 --> 01:39:43,280
What should we watch?

1061
01:39:45,840 --> 01:39:47,240
Do you like action?

1062
01:39:49,040 --> 01:39:50,920
No, not really.

1063
01:39:51,760 --> 01:39:55,280
What about a rom-com? I think I'd like that.

1064
01:39:55,280 --> 01:39:56,680
Then you pick.

1065
01:39:58,520 --> 01:40:01,360
There is this movie I've wanted to watch for a while.

1066
01:40:01,360 --> 01:40:02,320
I'll put that on.

1067
01:40:02,320 --> 01:40:03,400
Okay.

1068
01:40:12,640 --> 01:40:14,840
Here it is. She's a good actress.

1069
01:40:14,840 --> 01:40:17,240
But the male lead is really good,

1070
01:40:17,240 --> 01:40:19,240
and really handsome.

1071
01:40:26,560 --> 01:40:27,720
Hold on.

1072
01:40:27,720 --> 01:40:29,880
Let's get these.

1073
01:40:30,600 --> 01:40:31,640
Here you go.

1074
01:41:03,960 --> 01:41:08,000
I could watch your beautiful face, your smile for an entire lifetime.

1075
01:41:40,320 --> 01:41:42,120
That's ridiculous.

1076
01:41:42,520 --> 01:41:45,320
How can a woman not know she's in love?

1077
01:41:47,720 --> 01:41:49,600
I don't think it's the woman's fault,

1078
01:41:50,080 --> 01:41:51,320
the guy's a coward.

1079
01:41:51,680 --> 01:41:53,520
A real man would go after the woman he wants.

1080
01:41:53,920 --> 01:41:55,800
Love asks for courage.

1081
01:41:56,600 --> 01:41:58,600
But how can the man make a move

1082
01:41:58,640 --> 01:42:00,880
if the woman doesn't give a hint?

1083
01:42:02,280 --> 01:42:03,960
I'm glad the actor's really good.

1084
01:42:04,440 --> 01:42:06,000
I told you he's a good actor.

1085
01:42:06,040 --> 01:42:10,360
He's so handsome too and I bet he has a great personality, you can just tell.

1086
01:42:10,360 --> 01:42:12,080
I think he sucks at acting.

1087
01:42:12,120 --> 01:42:15,800
He's so pretentious too, I don't like this movie.

1088
01:42:15,800 --> 01:42:17,160
Let's watch something else.

1089
01:42:17,160 --> 01:42:20,120
I don't like romantic movies anyway.

1090
01:42:22,920 --> 01:42:25,360
He's so handsome, such a good actor. Whatever.

1091
01:42:28,120 --> 01:42:30,640
Let's just watch something else.

1092
01:42:32,280 --> 01:42:33,800
How about this?

1093
01:42:33,840 --> 01:42:36,280
There's a movie I really wanted to watch,

1094
01:42:36,320 --> 01:42:38,560
and the female lead is played by a gorgeous woman.

1095
01:42:38,600 --> 01:42:39,840
I think we should watch that.

1096
01:42:39,880 --> 01:42:41,200
Let's put it on.

1097
01:42:43,720 --> 01:42:45,400
A gorgeous woman, huh?

1098
01:42:46,640 --> 01:42:47,720
Did you say something?

1099
01:42:49,200 --> 01:42:50,800
No, I didn't.

1100
01:43:47,680 --> 01:43:48,760
Çiçek?

1101
01:43:50,440 --> 01:43:51,960
Stop pouting, please.

1102
01:43:55,360 --> 01:43:57,280
That guy's not worth it.

1103
01:43:58,720 --> 01:44:01,400
You've been ignoring me for days,

1104
01:44:02,240 --> 01:44:04,400
turning your head whenever you see me,

1105
01:44:05,400 --> 01:44:07,920
these shouldn't have been your first words to me, Berat.

1106
01:44:25,400 --> 01:44:26,840
Çiçek.

1107
01:44:28,080 --> 01:44:30,760
I lost my mind when I first heard what was going on.

1108
01:44:31,280 --> 01:44:34,600
What is there to get so angry about, Berat? I don't get it.

1109
01:44:34,640 --> 01:44:37,520
Just because I love a man.

1110
01:44:41,880 --> 01:44:46,160
And it's not just anyone either, it's Malik we're talking about.

1111
01:44:48,360 --> 01:44:50,320
He's been so good to us.

1112
01:44:51,200 --> 01:44:53,760
This is a man that put himself in danger,

1113
01:44:53,800 --> 01:44:56,520
went and talked to loan sharks to save you.

1114
01:44:57,840 --> 01:44:59,400
He paid off our debt.

1115
01:45:00,600 --> 01:45:03,080
Would he have done such a thing if he didn't love me?

1116
01:45:03,120 --> 01:45:05,400
Would he if he didn't love us?

1117
01:45:06,360 --> 01:45:07,840
He's one of us.

1118
01:45:09,760 --> 01:45:12,800
I only have you and mom in this world.

1119
01:45:17,040 --> 01:45:19,360
You both turned your back on me.

1120
01:45:19,400 --> 01:45:21,320
You left me alone.

1121
01:45:26,160 --> 01:45:28,640
And just because I loved a man.

1122
01:46:44,440 --> 01:46:46,520
You look so innocent.

1123
01:52:51,680 --> 01:52:54,000
It's time to go back soon.

1124
01:53:01,800 --> 01:53:04,120
I wish we could stay here forever.

1125
01:53:29,960 --> 01:53:32,240
Where are you, Çiçek? Where have you gone?

1126
01:53:32,240 --> 01:53:36,240
I've been looking around the house and the garden for hours.

1127
01:53:36,280 --> 01:53:38,640
You left work and diappeared again.

1128
01:53:54,440 --> 01:53:55,680
What do I do with you?

1129
01:53:55,720 --> 01:53:58,520
She went to meet up with him again.

1130
01:53:58,560 --> 01:54:01,120
She never listens to what I say.

1131
01:54:02,920 --> 01:54:05,520
I'll make you regret your every move, just you wait.

1132
01:54:08,640 --> 01:54:09,680
No.

1133
01:54:10,720 --> 01:54:12,080
No, this won't do.

1134
01:54:12,120 --> 01:54:15,320
Shouting and scolding won't do any good.

1135
01:54:15,360 --> 01:54:17,200
Putting it nicely didn't work.

1136
01:54:20,560 --> 01:54:22,640
I know what to do with you two.

1137
01:54:52,280 --> 01:54:54,040
She's so beautiful.

1138
01:54:55,000 --> 01:54:56,280
She's like a painting.

1139
01:55:29,320 --> 01:55:30,680
Good morning.

1140
01:55:31,880 --> 01:55:32,800
Good morning.

1141
01:55:34,560 --> 01:55:36,480
Did you sleep well?

1142
01:55:37,800 --> 01:55:39,920
Yes, I did.

1143
01:55:40,440 --> 01:55:42,720
I didn't have a nightmare either, that's a first.

1144
01:55:43,320 --> 01:55:46,280
I hope I didn't cause you any trouble going into the bedroom,

1145
01:55:47,040 --> 01:55:49,080
I don't remember how I woke up at all.

1146
01:55:50,280 --> 01:55:51,880
How did I come here?

1147
01:55:53,640 --> 01:55:55,280
No, it was no trouble.

1148
01:55:56,920 --> 01:55:58,120
I...

1149
01:55:59,800 --> 01:56:03,640
I fell asleep as well while I was putting you to bed.

1150
01:56:05,720 --> 01:56:07,160
We were both really tired.

1151
01:56:08,240 --> 01:56:09,480
That must be why.

1152
01:56:18,240 --> 01:56:19,920
Why can't I clasp this?

1153
01:56:47,840 --> 01:56:49,000
My heart.

1154
01:56:49,840 --> 01:56:52,000
I feel like my heart will beat out of its place.

1155
01:56:53,280 --> 01:56:55,240
Why is it beating so hard?

1156
01:57:12,400 --> 01:57:14,320
They must have returned.

1157
01:57:34,640 --> 01:57:36,640
Osman, where have you been?

1158
01:57:37,400 --> 01:57:40,360
I'm working as always, where else would I be?

1159
01:57:40,400 --> 01:57:43,720
One of your employees came to our branch office,

1160
01:57:43,720 --> 01:57:47,160
his name is Berat. He applied for a consumer loan.

1161
01:57:48,760 --> 01:57:49,760
And?

1162
01:57:50,200 --> 01:57:53,200
It's a large amount too, I thought I'd call and ask if you'd vouch for him.

1163
01:57:53,240 --> 01:57:54,360
Should I give him the loan?

1164
01:57:57,200 --> 01:57:58,640
So he came to you?

1165
01:57:59,720 --> 01:58:03,960
Osman, don't give any loan to him yet. Wait for me to get back to you.

1166
01:58:03,960 --> 01:58:05,800
Let me find out what's his issue.

1167
01:58:05,800 --> 01:58:08,000
If you say so. We'll deny him the loan.

1168
01:58:08,000 --> 01:58:10,880
You should stop by for some tea some time, brother.

1169
01:58:10,880 --> 01:58:13,640
Okay, I will stop by. Take care.

1170
01:58:23,240 --> 01:58:24,920
Money opens doors.

1171
01:58:25,520 --> 01:58:29,320
Maybe I can get information on the Karahan family from Berat.

1172
01:58:45,760 --> 01:58:46,880
Do tell, Uncle Durmuş.

1173
01:58:46,920 --> 01:58:49,480
How did the engagement go, did you get the girl?

1174
01:58:49,480 --> 01:58:51,120
We did.

1175
01:58:51,160 --> 01:58:53,160
The two of them had been in love

1176
01:58:53,200 --> 01:58:55,440
and seeing each other for a while.

1177
01:58:55,480 --> 01:58:57,400
The families gave their approval.

1178
01:58:57,440 --> 01:59:00,160
So, the rings were put on and they got engaged.

1179
01:59:01,480 --> 01:59:02,680
Congratulations.

1180
01:59:02,720 --> 01:59:03,960
Thank you.

1181
01:59:04,960 --> 01:59:07,840
Here are our coffees.

1182
01:59:07,880 --> 01:59:09,680
Thank you, dear.

1183
01:59:09,720 --> 01:59:11,720
Here you go, Güllü.

1184
01:59:13,000 --> 01:59:15,560
Thank you for the coffee, dear.

1185
01:59:17,000 --> 01:59:18,280
Enjoy.

1186
01:59:26,120 --> 01:59:27,480
Enjoy.

1187
01:59:28,480 --> 01:59:29,400
Thanks.

1188
01:59:34,400 --> 01:59:37,560
My dear Mercan, you're so diligent.

1189
01:59:38,200 --> 01:59:40,760
They made soup too, we got lucky.

1190
01:59:44,400 --> 01:59:46,360
The soup recipe is all Ateş'.

1191
01:59:50,200 --> 01:59:51,960
I'm not saying this because she's my wife,

1192
01:59:52,560 --> 01:59:54,360
she's really skilled in the kitchen.

1193
01:59:55,560 --> 01:59:58,040
Don't say that. Didn't it turn out well in the end?

1194
01:59:58,080 --> 02:00:01,040
Of course it did. Thank you for your cooking.

1195
02:00:01,800 --> 02:00:03,520
You're my teacher after all.

1196
02:00:03,520 --> 02:00:06,800
But be careful, the student could become the master.

1197
02:00:08,520 --> 02:00:11,600
You have a long way to go before you beat the master.

1198
02:00:13,160 --> 02:00:16,080
I'm not saying this because I don't want you to,

1199
02:00:17,240 --> 02:00:18,920
I'm looking forward to those days.

1200
02:00:25,000 --> 02:00:26,320
May god protect you.

1201
02:00:26,320 --> 02:00:29,080
This place really did you some good.

1202
02:00:29,120 --> 02:00:32,880
But it seems like you're bickering a little bit.

1203
02:00:34,720 --> 02:00:38,040
That's love for you, love causes that.

1204
02:01:15,080 --> 02:01:16,120
Ms. Zahide?

1205
02:01:16,120 --> 02:01:17,760
You scared me.

1206
02:01:18,560 --> 02:01:20,280
Don't be scared.

1207
02:01:20,840 --> 02:01:21,680
What's going on?

1208
02:01:21,720 --> 02:01:24,200
How the kitty doing, is there any improvement?

1209
02:01:24,240 --> 02:01:28,320
The vet says she's been a real soldier.

1210
02:01:28,320 --> 02:01:30,840
Our kitten turned out to be one tough nut.

1211
02:01:30,880 --> 02:01:33,520
She had her food, and her water.

1212
02:01:33,560 --> 02:01:35,120
I'm happy to hear that.

1213
02:01:39,240 --> 02:01:40,400
What is it?

1214
02:01:40,440 --> 02:01:42,120
What do you mean?

1215
02:01:42,120 --> 02:01:44,120
You're staring at me.

1216
02:01:45,280 --> 02:01:46,280
What am I staring at?

1217
02:01:46,280 --> 02:01:48,400
You're staring at me right now.

1218
02:01:48,440 --> 02:01:49,840
I'm staring at you?

1219
02:01:49,880 --> 02:01:51,000
You are.

1220
02:01:52,360 --> 02:01:53,440
I'm staring at you?

1221
02:01:53,440 --> 02:01:55,720
Why would I, why would I stare at you?

1222
02:01:55,720 --> 02:01:56,720
Okay, Mr. Yaşar.

1223
02:01:56,760 --> 02:01:59,800
Let's pretend the last 2 minutes never happened,

1224
02:01:59,840 --> 02:02:02,440
let's erase this moment from our minds, it's gone.

1225
02:02:02,480 --> 02:02:06,360
Burak, you take that file and leave it in Mr. Ateş' room already.

1226
02:02:06,400 --> 02:02:08,360
Okay, Ms. Zahide. I'm on it.

1227
02:02:14,320 --> 02:02:15,600
Hi, what's up?

1228
02:02:33,640 --> 02:02:35,120
Could you check this again?

1229
02:02:35,120 --> 02:02:36,720
Burak?

1230
02:02:38,160 --> 02:02:40,000
Are things a little off between you

1231
02:02:40,040 --> 02:02:41,880
and Ms. Demet or am I seeing thing?

1232
02:02:43,600 --> 02:02:46,840
Nothing's off with Demet, but things are off with her brother.

1233
02:02:46,840 --> 02:02:49,240
He taught me a good lesson.

1234
02:02:52,960 --> 02:02:55,200
He's right in a sense.

1235
02:02:55,200 --> 02:02:56,760
I'm nothing next to Demet.

1236
02:02:56,760 --> 02:02:58,880
What would she have to do with a guy like me?

1237
02:03:00,520 --> 02:03:01,640
We'll check it later.

1238
02:03:22,400 --> 02:03:23,920
Speak, Ziya.

1239
02:03:23,960 --> 02:03:26,760
I found some information on Cemal, Haydar.

1240
02:03:26,800 --> 02:03:29,320
What is it? Tell me, I'm listening.

1241
02:03:29,360 --> 02:03:31,920
This Cemal is an orphan,

1242
02:03:31,960 --> 02:03:34,280
he was homeless for a while when he was

1243
02:03:34,320 --> 02:03:36,600
a kid, then he stayed at an orphanage where he grew up.

1244
02:03:38,320 --> 02:03:41,080
Ateş is also an orphan who grew up in an orphanage.

1245
02:03:41,120 --> 02:03:44,680
Maybe they stayed at the same place.

1246
02:03:44,720 --> 02:03:45,640
Maybe.

1247
02:03:45,640 --> 02:03:51,120
I'll get the guys to ask around, if there's any news, I'll call you.

1248
02:03:51,160 --> 02:03:54,000
Okay, I'll wait for your call.

1249
02:03:57,480 --> 02:03:59,600
First, I'll find out who you are,

1250
02:04:00,760 --> 02:04:04,640
then, I'll prepare you a wonderful end, Ateş Karahan.

1251
02:04:29,560 --> 02:04:30,760
Does it feel different?

1252
02:04:33,280 --> 02:04:34,280
No.

1253
02:04:35,080 --> 02:04:36,480
It feels like...

1254
02:04:37,920 --> 02:04:42,120
We'd been gone for a long time and only just have arrived.

1255
02:04:42,120 --> 02:04:43,960
It's a strange feeling.

1256
02:04:45,240 --> 02:04:46,320
Are you tired?

1257
02:04:46,360 --> 02:04:47,680
No, I'm not.

1258
02:04:48,640 --> 02:04:51,680
We came back to our room after traveling to distant lands.

1259
02:04:51,680 --> 02:04:53,480
But I'm not tired.

1260
02:04:58,320 --> 02:04:59,480
Yes.

1261
02:05:00,880 --> 02:05:02,280
We came back to our room.

1262
02:05:14,880 --> 02:05:16,320
I'll go wash up.

1263
02:05:25,280 --> 02:05:26,400
Our room?

1264
02:05:27,680 --> 02:05:29,360
Why did I say that?

1265
02:05:30,960 --> 02:05:32,280
Whatever.

1266
02:06:42,280 --> 02:06:46,200
But this is the ring Nezir bought.

1267
02:06:53,120 --> 02:06:54,600
What's this doing here?

1268
02:07:01,960 --> 02:07:03,640
What are you looking at so intently?

1269
02:07:36,040 --> 02:07:37,560
Whose ring is this?

1270
02:08:03,800 --> 02:08:05,840
What's this doing here?

1271
02:09:17,000 --> 02:09:19,120
What's this ring doing here?

1272
02:09:21,960 --> 02:09:25,200
I honestly don't know, it was on the dresser.

1273
02:09:25,920 --> 02:09:27,760
How did this ring end up in this room?

1274
02:09:29,120 --> 02:09:31,440
I'm just as shocked as you, I promise.

1275
02:09:32,480 --> 02:09:33,880
Where had you put this ring?

1276
02:09:37,120 --> 02:09:40,400
Since that day... I mean the day that I...

1277
02:09:40,400 --> 02:09:43,240
I don't know, I didn't even keep it.

1278
02:09:43,240 --> 02:09:45,960
I truly don't understand how it's here.

1279
02:09:47,520 --> 02:09:49,520
I saw it sitting on the dresser when I came.

1280
02:09:49,760 --> 02:09:51,880
How did this ring end up in this room, then?

1281
02:09:54,160 --> 02:09:56,920
Listen to me, please believe me.

1282
02:09:58,400 --> 02:09:59,720
I didn't do anything wrong.

1283
02:09:59,720 --> 02:10:02,680
I've had nothing to do with that ring, I really don't know.

1284
02:10:03,600 --> 02:10:06,120
Maybe my mom had it, or...

1285
02:10:07,560 --> 02:10:09,440
I truly have no idea, I don't know.

1286
02:10:15,480 --> 02:10:17,280
Where are you going?

1287
02:10:24,840 --> 02:10:26,240
Enjoy your coffees.

1288
02:10:32,880 --> 02:10:34,720
Who put this trash in our room?

1289
02:10:42,800 --> 02:10:44,000
What's going on here?

1290
02:10:44,920 --> 02:10:47,480
Who put this trash in our room?

1291
02:11:16,320 --> 02:11:18,080
Isn't this Mercan's trash?

1292
02:11:19,000 --> 02:11:20,160
Why don't you ask her?

1293
02:11:20,400 --> 02:11:21,840
Why are you asking us?

1294
02:11:22,160 --> 02:11:24,960
She must have kept it as a souvenir from her engagement to Nezir.

1295
02:11:25,000 --> 02:11:26,080
Aslı!

1296
02:11:28,200 --> 02:11:30,160
Do I have to warn you?

1297
02:11:31,120 --> 02:11:32,440
Is she wrong?

1298
02:11:32,440 --> 02:11:34,400
Wasn't she engaged to that man?

1299
02:11:34,440 --> 02:11:36,720
The ring must be theirs.

1300
02:11:36,760 --> 02:11:38,400
She's obviously kept it since.

1301
02:11:38,440 --> 02:11:39,680
Why are you asking us?

1302
02:11:43,480 --> 02:11:45,080
Mercan didn't keep keep this.

1303
02:11:51,920 --> 02:11:53,240
I know.

1304
02:12:05,040 --> 02:12:06,600
She wouldn't do such a thing.

1305
02:12:11,920 --> 02:12:16,480
If this ring didn't just grow wings and fly into our room,

1306
02:12:16,520 --> 02:12:18,520
one of you put it there.

1307
02:12:21,280 --> 02:12:23,080
Tell me, which one of you did it?

1308
02:12:36,160 --> 02:12:37,960
I put it there Mr. Ateş.

1309
02:12:39,960 --> 02:12:42,200
I found it on the ground while I was cleaning,

1310
02:12:44,400 --> 02:12:47,760
when I saw the name I figured it'd been misplaced, so I put it there.

1311
02:12:48,080 --> 02:12:49,240
I'm sorry.

1312
02:12:49,880 --> 02:12:51,880
I don't want this nonsense repeated.

1313
02:12:53,200 --> 02:12:54,360
Be more careful.

1314
02:13:04,480 --> 02:13:05,960
Throw that in the trash.

1315
02:13:09,880 --> 02:13:11,080
Come with me.

1316
02:13:57,480 --> 02:13:58,760
Where are we going?

1317
02:14:01,800 --> 02:14:02,960
We?

1318
02:14:04,480 --> 02:14:08,240
I'm going to the company, are you coming with me?

1319
02:14:09,520 --> 02:14:11,040
I have permission?

1320
02:14:11,560 --> 02:14:13,120
You said you wanted to work.

1321
02:14:14,520 --> 02:14:15,640
I do.

1322
02:14:16,040 --> 02:14:19,440
I just got a little surprised by the way you said it.

1323
02:14:19,440 --> 02:14:22,200
But I'm glad. I'd gotten really bored sititng at home.

1324
02:14:22,240 --> 02:14:24,480
Work must have piled up at the company, too.

1325
02:14:26,080 --> 02:14:27,520
Will you come with me,

1326
02:14:28,880 --> 02:14:30,920
or will you keep chatting here?

1327
02:14:32,760 --> 02:14:34,080
I'll come.

1328
02:14:34,800 --> 02:14:36,200
Let's go, then.

1329
02:14:46,760 --> 02:14:47,960
What is it now?

1330
02:14:50,200 --> 02:14:52,200
What you just did...

1331
02:14:53,360 --> 02:14:54,360
What did I do?

1332
02:14:55,480 --> 02:14:57,120
You know what you did.

1333
02:14:57,560 --> 02:14:58,880
Thank you.

1334
02:15:00,800 --> 02:15:01,880
I don't understand.

1335
02:15:01,920 --> 02:15:03,680
Why are you thanking me?

1336
02:15:05,920 --> 02:15:09,000
For believing in me, trusting me.

1337
02:15:09,800 --> 02:15:12,400
I don't need to trust you to see you're telling the truth.

1338
02:15:16,120 --> 02:15:18,960
You'd have to be stupid not to see it.

1339
02:15:22,360 --> 02:15:24,160
The ring was in an unusual spot in our room,

1340
02:15:24,200 --> 02:15:25,840
it was obvious someone had put it there.

1341
02:15:26,880 --> 02:15:28,360
This is evil, you know.

1342
02:15:29,440 --> 02:15:32,440
Zehra came forward, there's obviously been a misunderstanding.

1343
02:15:32,480 --> 02:15:34,720
There is no reason fror her to lie.

1344
02:15:35,680 --> 02:15:36,960
I hope that's the case.

1345
02:15:38,080 --> 02:15:39,480
Thank you anyway.

1346
02:15:41,680 --> 02:15:44,160
For standing by me in front of everyone.

1347
02:15:44,160 --> 02:15:46,000
I thought that was really great.

1348
02:15:52,000 --> 02:15:54,560
I told you I'd always be there for you.

1349
02:15:58,680 --> 02:16:00,320
I keep my promises, usually.

1350
02:16:02,680 --> 02:16:03,960
So you said.

1351
02:16:10,840 --> 02:16:11,880
Oh no!

1352
02:16:14,880 --> 02:16:16,360
My necklace.

1353
02:16:16,920 --> 02:16:18,920
It's just a necklace, why are you so upset?

1354
02:16:18,960 --> 02:16:20,080
Forget about it.

1355
02:16:21,160 --> 02:16:22,480
Did it have sentimental value?

1356
02:16:23,680 --> 02:16:25,480
No but I liked it.

1357
02:16:26,640 --> 02:16:29,920
You were always playing with it, I thought it had some meaning.

1358
02:16:30,560 --> 02:16:31,520
Whatever.

1359
02:16:32,240 --> 02:16:33,480
There's nothing we can do.

1360
02:16:34,040 --> 02:16:35,120
It's broken.

1361
02:16:41,200 --> 02:16:45,200
I'm asking one last time, are you coming with me?

1362
02:16:47,960 --> 02:16:49,120
Always.

1363
02:16:58,720 --> 02:17:01,160
I mean, I'd always come with you if it's

1364
02:17:01,160 --> 02:17:03,320
to the company, that's what I meant.

1365
02:17:05,560 --> 02:17:06,680
Let's go, then.

1366
02:17:09,360 --> 02:17:10,960
Go ahead, Ms. Mercan.

1367
02:18:03,920 --> 02:18:05,440
You're so beautiful,

1368
02:18:06,800 --> 02:18:08,160
and you're mine.

1369
02:18:13,760 --> 02:18:15,800
You just don't know it yet.

1370
02:18:16,960 --> 02:18:19,000
But it's only a matter of time, Mercan.

1371
02:18:19,000 --> 02:18:22,160
Both you and him will realize this soon.

1372
02:18:29,600 --> 02:18:31,080
What does this mean, Nezir?

1373
02:18:31,920 --> 02:18:33,240
What are you talking about?

1374
02:18:33,240 --> 02:18:35,160
Why did you bear down on Burak?

1375
02:18:35,560 --> 02:18:37,120
Why did you threaten him?

1376
02:18:38,960 --> 02:18:40,640
He already told you?

1377
02:18:40,640 --> 02:18:42,000
Was he terrified?

1378
02:18:44,200 --> 02:18:47,360
Listen to me, Demet. You stay away from cowardly and chatty men,

1379
02:18:47,400 --> 02:18:48,800
they won't do you any good.

1380
02:18:49,640 --> 02:18:52,520
Burak didn't tell me, I found out on my own.

1381
02:18:52,560 --> 02:18:54,240
But that's not the point.

1382
02:18:56,000 --> 02:18:58,200
Why did you do something so despicable?

1383
02:18:59,920 --> 02:19:03,080
I'm only protecting my sister from the wolves around her.

1384
02:19:04,800 --> 02:19:06,680
I don't need protection.

1385
02:19:07,160 --> 02:19:09,520
Face the fact that I'm all grown up

1386
02:19:09,560 --> 02:19:12,120
and can make my own decisions, already.

1387
02:19:14,560 --> 02:19:17,240
I've had the necessary talk with that punk already,

1388
02:19:17,560 --> 02:19:19,200
now I'm having it with you.

1389
02:19:20,520 --> 02:19:22,680
You will stay away from one another.

1390
02:19:23,400 --> 02:19:27,240
You may be an adult, but you grew up in a bubble.

1391
02:19:28,080 --> 02:19:31,520
You have no idea how awful the world, and how dirty people can get.

1392
02:19:31,560 --> 02:19:36,400
Don't worry, Nezir. I learned how bad people can be from you.

1393
02:19:40,880 --> 02:19:42,720
I'll talk to whomever I want,

1394
02:19:43,400 --> 02:19:45,600
see whomever I want.

1395
02:19:46,320 --> 02:19:48,160
You will respect that.

1396
02:19:55,240 --> 02:19:56,680
There's no way, dear.

1397
02:20:01,200 --> 02:20:06,000
If saying it nicely doesn't work, I'll use harsher methods.

1398
02:20:15,680 --> 02:20:17,240
What do you think?

1399
02:20:18,200 --> 02:20:20,200
So, what have you been up to?

1400
02:20:20,240 --> 02:20:23,680
Did you get around to doing what I asked you to?

1401
02:20:25,080 --> 02:20:27,640
That will be resolved in a few days, anyway.

1402
02:20:27,680 --> 02:20:30,000
We'll act accordingly from then on, alright.

1403
02:20:30,040 --> 02:20:31,960
Okay, then.

1404
02:20:32,640 --> 02:20:37,360
Okay, then. I'll talk to you later, take care.

1405
02:20:37,360 --> 02:20:38,400
Bye.

1406
02:20:40,000 --> 02:20:41,000
Mom?

1407
02:20:43,080 --> 02:20:44,720
What's going on, what's resolving itself?

1408
02:20:46,600 --> 02:20:49,160
Have you changed the sheets at the house?

1409
02:20:49,200 --> 02:20:51,160
Yes, I just got done with it.

1410
02:20:51,200 --> 02:20:52,360
Okay, good.

1411
02:20:52,760 --> 02:20:56,360
Now take these to the other kitchen, the one in the house.

1412
02:20:56,760 --> 02:20:57,920
Okay.

1413
02:21:02,600 --> 02:21:04,720
You forced me to do this.

1414
02:21:05,320 --> 02:21:06,960
You left me no other option.

1415
02:21:12,760 --> 02:21:13,960
I'll do it.

1416
02:21:14,640 --> 02:21:15,800
I'll get it done.

1417
02:21:16,200 --> 02:21:17,360
I'll kill her.

1418
02:21:18,080 --> 02:21:19,680
I'll kill her this time.

1419
02:21:19,680 --> 02:21:22,200
I'll have no peace as long as that girl's alive.

1420
02:21:29,160 --> 02:21:30,640
You said you'd deal with it.

1421
02:21:32,360 --> 02:21:34,680
You said he wouldn't even want to look at her after this.

1422
02:21:35,400 --> 02:21:37,880
They've already established trust between them.

1423
02:21:38,560 --> 02:21:40,400
You saw what happened downstairs.

1424
02:21:41,360 --> 02:21:42,360
You saw it.

1425
02:21:43,440 --> 02:21:44,560
What's going on?

1426
02:21:45,080 --> 02:21:48,480
She's taking the man I love from me right in front of our eyes.

1427
02:21:50,840 --> 02:21:52,440
I can't stand this any longer.

1428
02:21:52,440 --> 02:21:55,200
Aslı, keep your voice down. Someone will hear.

1429
02:21:56,240 --> 02:21:57,320
Let them hear.

1430
02:21:57,360 --> 02:21:58,720
Let them hear!

1431
02:21:59,280 --> 02:22:00,320
He's mine!

1432
02:22:00,320 --> 02:22:01,960
Ateş is mine.

1433
02:22:01,960 --> 02:22:03,800
I'll kill that girl.

1434
02:22:04,440 --> 02:22:05,640
I'll end her.

1435
02:22:08,160 --> 02:22:09,440
Everyone should hear it.

1436
02:22:12,160 --> 02:22:13,600
Enough, I've had enough!

1437
02:22:20,520 --> 02:22:21,600
Mom.

1438
02:22:22,760 --> 02:22:25,880
Mom, you saw how he protected Mercan.

1439
02:22:25,920 --> 02:22:27,720
I can't stand it, mom.

1440
02:22:27,720 --> 02:22:29,160
Stop your crying!

1441
02:22:29,680 --> 02:22:30,840
Stand tall.

1442
02:22:33,000 --> 02:22:34,240
I feel like I'm dying.

1443
02:22:34,240 --> 02:22:35,840
Don't you see?

1444
02:22:37,920 --> 02:22:40,720
I'm begging you, please do something.

1445
02:22:41,720 --> 02:22:43,320
Don't let Ateş love that girl.

1446
02:22:43,320 --> 02:22:46,920
Make him hate her, I want nothing else!

1447
02:22:48,840 --> 02:22:49,840
Okay.

1448
02:22:50,480 --> 02:22:53,320
The bond between them is stronger than I thought.

1449
02:22:53,840 --> 02:22:56,360
Then, we'll make a stronger move.

1450
02:22:56,400 --> 02:22:59,400
No move is enough to come between them, don't you see?

1451
02:23:00,360 --> 02:23:02,320
Ateş is already head over heels for her!

1452
02:23:03,320 --> 02:23:05,720
I can see it in his eyes.

1453
02:23:06,240 --> 02:23:07,680
We're too late.

1454
02:23:07,720 --> 02:23:09,200
I've had enough!

1455
02:23:09,200 --> 02:23:10,400
Shut up!

1456
02:23:12,480 --> 02:23:15,560
Stop whining like a spoiled little girl, enough!

1457
02:23:15,600 --> 02:23:19,280
You can't break down every time you lose, grow up already!

1458
02:23:22,040 --> 02:23:24,000
Call Nezir and give me the phone.

1459
02:23:25,600 --> 02:23:26,680
Why?

1460
02:23:26,720 --> 02:23:28,240
I have an idea.

1461
02:23:28,920 --> 02:23:31,680
Something that will put an end to this Ateş and Mercan business.

1462
02:23:31,720 --> 02:23:33,720
It seems there's no other way.

1463
02:23:34,480 --> 02:23:35,680
Call him now.

1464
02:23:53,040 --> 02:23:54,480
Hello, Nezir?

1465
02:23:55,880 --> 02:23:57,280
It's Müzeyyen.

1466
02:23:58,040 --> 02:23:59,640
Listen to me carefully.

1467
02:24:13,480 --> 02:24:14,480
Malik!

1468
02:24:14,760 --> 02:24:16,040
Go away!

1469
02:24:16,040 --> 02:24:17,400
Why did you come here?

1470
02:24:18,480 --> 02:24:20,320
I missed you so much, Çiçek.

1471
02:24:20,320 --> 02:24:21,560
I had to see you.

1472
02:24:21,560 --> 02:24:23,040
Me too.

1473
02:24:23,720 --> 02:24:27,000
It's awful not being able to stand next to you, to talk to you.

1474
02:24:27,480 --> 02:24:29,600
You have no idea.

1475
02:24:32,040 --> 02:24:34,200
My favorite person in the world is two steps

1476
02:24:34,240 --> 02:24:36,480
away from me, but I can't go and talk to her.

1477
02:24:37,640 --> 02:24:42,200
Don't talk like that. Everything's already a mess and I'm upset enough.

1478
02:24:44,520 --> 02:24:45,720
Let me tell you something.

1479
02:24:46,400 --> 02:24:48,600
Mom was back to normal this morning.

1480
02:24:49,200 --> 02:24:50,960
I think she's warming up to the idea.

1481
02:24:52,080 --> 02:24:55,920
Who knows? Maybe she won't be upset with us and accept our relationship.

1482
02:24:56,600 --> 02:24:57,880
Do you really think so?

1483
02:24:57,880 --> 02:24:59,120
I really do.

1484
02:25:02,120 --> 02:25:04,000
Okay, then.

1485
02:25:04,520 --> 02:25:06,360
Let's not act out of line.

1486
02:25:06,400 --> 02:25:07,560
Try to appease her.

1487
02:25:08,680 --> 02:25:11,760
I said this would happen, I said it would work itself out.

1488
02:25:11,800 --> 02:25:13,800
Everything will be great.

1489
02:25:13,840 --> 02:25:15,320
I hope so.

1490
02:25:19,200 --> 02:25:20,760
Is someone coming here?

1491
02:25:24,280 --> 02:25:25,880
Okay, no one's around. Go away.

1492
02:25:25,880 --> 02:25:28,440
Let's not get caught when things are looking up.

1493
02:25:29,560 --> 02:25:30,760
Go, get out.

1494
02:26:00,520 --> 02:26:01,880
Are you not coming?

1495
02:26:03,320 --> 02:26:04,480
I have some business.

1496
02:26:06,120 --> 02:26:07,200
What business?

1497
02:26:08,320 --> 02:26:09,440
Just some business.

1498
02:26:10,600 --> 02:26:12,640
I'm asking you what business you have.

1499
02:26:13,080 --> 02:26:14,280
Are you interrogating me?

1500
02:26:16,080 --> 02:26:18,360
Why are acting so cold toward me out of a sudden?

1501
02:26:18,400 --> 02:26:19,240
I'm not acting cold.

1502
02:26:19,280 --> 02:26:20,360
You are.

1503
02:26:21,520 --> 02:26:23,200
Okay, I am.

1504
02:26:23,600 --> 02:26:25,040
Are you satisfied now?

1505
02:26:25,080 --> 02:26:26,120
I am.

1506
02:26:26,120 --> 02:26:27,320
I'm delighted.

1507
02:26:27,880 --> 02:26:29,400
Why are you being so cold?

1508
02:26:31,000 --> 02:26:34,600
I merely asked what business you had to attend to, I guess I shouldn't have.

1509
02:26:35,000 --> 02:26:36,000
You shouldn't.

1510
02:26:37,080 --> 02:26:40,280
Since when do we let each other know where we're going?

1511
02:26:40,800 --> 02:26:41,960
Am I missing something?

1512
02:26:42,640 --> 02:26:43,720
You're right.

1513
02:26:44,160 --> 02:26:45,480
You're not missing anything.

1514
02:26:46,120 --> 02:26:47,680
We haven't gotten anywhere.

1515
02:26:51,920 --> 02:26:53,680
I was just asking.

1516
02:26:53,840 --> 02:26:56,600
It's not like I care where you go or what you do.

1517
02:26:57,040 --> 02:26:59,040
It's none of my concern, it's not my business.

1518
02:27:00,720 --> 02:27:03,560
From now on, you won't ask me either and we won't have any problems.

1519
02:27:06,600 --> 02:27:08,360
That's out of line.

1520
02:27:22,400 --> 02:27:23,760
He's walking contradiction.

1521
02:27:53,160 --> 02:27:55,760
We're not seeing eye to eye, we're not on the same page.

1522
02:27:57,880 --> 02:27:59,520
But you're invaluable to me.

1523
02:28:01,680 --> 02:28:03,400
I don't want us to be on bad terms.

1524
02:28:05,160 --> 02:28:08,200
I don't like to see someone so dear to me, with men of lower ranks.

1525
02:28:09,920 --> 02:28:12,040
I hope you can understand, Demet, my dear sister.

1526
02:28:13,480 --> 02:28:18,080
This is a natural consequence of being so valuable and loved, Demet.

1527
02:28:22,320 --> 02:28:24,240
I thought you were here to apologize.

1528
02:28:24,800 --> 02:28:26,640
But you're just the same.

1529
02:28:28,960 --> 02:28:31,080
The one who made the mistake should apologize.

1530
02:28:31,680 --> 02:28:33,720
I'm not making a mistake, I'm being your brother.

1531
02:28:42,520 --> 02:28:44,600
And I'm keeping you from making mistakes.

1532
02:28:45,520 --> 02:28:47,520
You will not see each other.

1533
02:28:50,200 --> 02:28:51,280
Are we clear?

1534
02:29:00,720 --> 02:29:01,800
He's so annoying.

1535
02:29:15,680 --> 02:29:17,840
How is the kitten doing, Ms. Zahide?

1536
02:29:18,640 --> 02:29:21,720
She got all her vaccinations, she's much better now.

1537
02:29:21,720 --> 02:29:23,360
I'm happy to hear that.

1538
02:29:23,960 --> 02:29:25,520
Will you adopt her?

1539
02:29:25,640 --> 02:29:28,480
Of course not, I already have three cats.

1540
02:29:28,520 --> 02:29:29,800
I'll find a home for her.

1541
02:29:29,840 --> 02:29:30,880
I can't take her.

1542
02:29:31,720 --> 02:29:34,480
I'd love to take her in, if I didn't already have two.

1543
02:29:35,040 --> 02:29:36,840
Cats are beautiful creatures.

1544
02:29:36,880 --> 02:29:39,320
It's lovely to have another voice, another breath at home.

1545
02:29:39,640 --> 02:29:41,360
Loneliness is awful.

1546
02:29:43,480 --> 02:29:47,240
Having a life partner alongside the cats would be wonderful.

1547
02:29:47,560 --> 02:29:49,080
I'd honestly be delighted.

1548
02:29:49,080 --> 02:29:51,280
Then, it'd be an actual home.

1549
02:29:53,480 --> 02:29:56,360
I lost my phone, have you seen it?

1550
02:29:56,800 --> 02:29:57,880
I haven't seen it.

1551
02:30:04,240 --> 02:30:05,640
I'll ring you.

1552
02:30:07,160 --> 02:30:08,240
That'd be great.

1553
02:30:18,400 --> 02:30:19,360
It's off.

1554
02:30:19,360 --> 02:30:20,440
Nezir?

1555
02:30:21,160 --> 02:30:22,480
Have you seen my phone?

1556
02:30:23,040 --> 02:30:25,800
How would I know where your phone is? Check your space.

1557
02:30:31,600 --> 02:30:33,080
Did I leave it at home?

1558
02:30:38,800 --> 02:30:40,040
I should go check.

1559
02:30:40,080 --> 02:30:42,760
It's not like I could work now that Nezir's upset me so much.

1560
02:30:43,680 --> 02:30:45,080
You guys take care.

1561
02:30:45,360 --> 02:30:46,480
You too.

1562
02:30:47,160 --> 02:30:48,840
What's wrong with these two?

1563
02:30:53,480 --> 02:30:54,720
It's strange.

1564
02:30:54,720 --> 02:30:56,200
It's really strange.

1565
02:31:08,640 --> 02:31:10,040
Where have you been, man?

1566
02:31:10,280 --> 02:31:11,720
I was trying to park the car.

1567
02:31:11,720 --> 02:31:12,800
What is it?

1568
02:31:12,840 --> 02:31:14,920
Why did you call me here, is there something wrong?

1569
02:31:16,640 --> 02:31:17,880
Did Haydar do something?

1570
02:31:18,240 --> 02:31:19,240
Is it Nezir?

1571
02:31:19,280 --> 02:31:20,640
Did Nezir set us up again?

1572
02:31:20,640 --> 02:31:22,520
No, it's not something like that.

1573
02:31:22,960 --> 02:31:24,680
But it's important, I need your help.

1574
02:31:25,400 --> 02:31:27,880
But it's supposed to stay a secret between us, okay?

1575
02:31:27,920 --> 02:31:31,480
Don't be ridiculous. Have I ever blabbed to anyone before?

1576
02:31:32,560 --> 02:31:34,360
Mercan's necklace broke,

1577
02:31:34,960 --> 02:31:36,760
I need to get her a necklace.

1578
02:31:37,240 --> 02:31:39,920
You're better at this stuff than I am, could you help me?

1579
02:31:40,800 --> 02:31:41,920
Cemal, stop.

1580
02:31:44,320 --> 02:31:45,600
Only out of kindness.

1581
02:31:45,840 --> 02:31:46,880
That's why.

1582
02:31:46,880 --> 02:31:48,920
Of course it's out of kindness, why else?

1583
02:31:48,920 --> 02:31:51,440
I mean if that girl doesn't have a

1584
02:31:51,480 --> 02:31:54,440
necklace, what would happen to humanity?

1585
02:31:54,480 --> 02:31:55,560
Cemal.

1586
02:31:56,320 --> 02:31:57,400
Cut it out.

1587
02:32:01,120 --> 02:32:04,400
When the topic is Mercan, you're the one who goes overboard, not me.

1588
02:32:04,440 --> 02:32:07,320
Let me tell you this, you're going to end up making a mess again.

1589
02:32:07,360 --> 02:32:10,080
If you say another word, I swear I'm going to change my mind.

1590
02:32:11,800 --> 02:32:12,920
Let's go.

1591
02:32:19,880 --> 02:32:22,000
His reaction to this ring business was weird.

1592
02:32:22,800 --> 02:32:25,160
Things are starting to seem

1593
02:32:25,160 --> 02:32:27,840
really strange to me, Haydar.

1594
02:32:29,280 --> 02:32:31,440
He acted as though he was actually her husband.

1595
02:32:33,080 --> 02:32:34,960
There must be a real spark between them.

1596
02:32:39,560 --> 02:32:41,600
He must have fallen for our daughter.

1597
02:32:42,040 --> 02:32:43,520
What are you talking about, Nermin?

1598
02:32:44,120 --> 02:32:45,200
Don't speak nonsense.

1599
02:32:45,240 --> 02:32:47,880
I'm doing everything in my power to get rid of them

1600
02:32:47,880 --> 02:32:50,520
and you're talking about love. Don't be ridiculous.

1601
02:32:51,280 --> 02:32:52,320
God give me patience.

1602
02:32:53,240 --> 02:32:54,360
My god, give me patience.

1603
02:32:59,560 --> 02:33:00,680
Yes?

1604
02:33:01,200 --> 02:33:02,280
I'm listening, tell me.

1605
02:33:06,040 --> 02:33:07,080
Okay.

1606
02:33:07,640 --> 02:33:10,560
Okay, you keep looking into it. I'll be waiting for your call.

1607
02:33:14,880 --> 02:33:16,600
What are you looking into, Haydar?

1608
02:33:17,680 --> 02:33:19,160
What are you after this time?

1609
02:33:26,280 --> 02:33:28,960
I found the orphanage Cemal stayed at, I've looked into it.

1610
02:33:29,640 --> 02:33:31,840
It's the same orphanage Ateş claimed he stayed at.

1611
02:33:34,160 --> 02:33:35,200
So?

1612
02:33:35,200 --> 02:33:36,440
So what?

1613
02:33:40,840 --> 02:33:42,880
No one there knows about Ateş, Nermin.

1614
02:33:43,800 --> 02:33:44,920
What do you mean?

1615
02:33:47,240 --> 02:33:48,920
He lied to us.

1616
02:33:49,280 --> 02:33:51,560
Cemal was the one who stayed there, not Ateş.

1617
02:33:52,120 --> 02:33:54,000
If they set us up like this, there must

1618
02:33:54,040 --> 02:33:55,960
be something they don't want us to know.

1619
02:34:00,440 --> 02:34:02,360
We've got a clue, Nermin.

1620
02:34:02,520 --> 02:34:04,280
But you won't say anything to anyone

1621
02:34:04,280 --> 02:34:06,000
about this, including Mercan. Okay?

1622
02:34:06,920 --> 02:34:08,000
Okay, I won't.

1623
02:34:11,120 --> 02:34:13,440
Let's trace that clue back to see where it starts.

1624
02:34:14,280 --> 02:34:15,720
Let's see where it leads us.

1625
02:34:32,240 --> 02:34:34,040
That man was really patient with us.

1626
02:34:34,800 --> 02:34:35,920
Why did you say that?

1627
02:34:35,920 --> 02:34:39,480
We must have overwhelmed him with our questions and wishes.

1628
02:34:41,160 --> 02:34:42,280
But I think,

1629
02:34:43,200 --> 02:34:44,600
one needs to be attentive.

1630
02:34:48,880 --> 02:34:50,680
She looks good in delicate pieces.

1631
02:34:53,320 --> 02:34:54,920
It should have a meaning.

1632
02:34:59,200 --> 02:35:00,760
It should be like her.

1633
02:35:02,320 --> 02:35:03,520
What do you mean?

1634
02:35:03,520 --> 02:35:05,040
What do you mean, like her?

1635
02:35:06,320 --> 02:35:08,200
"Would the lady like this one?"

1636
02:35:08,240 --> 02:35:11,600
"We're looking for something simpler, more delicate."

1637
02:35:12,160 --> 02:35:13,600
"I want the stone to be a coral."

1638
02:35:14,520 --> 02:35:16,680
"The price is not an issue, we're looking

1639
02:35:16,680 --> 02:35:18,720
for something more valuable and chic."

1640
02:35:18,760 --> 02:35:20,080
Cemal.

1641
02:35:20,680 --> 02:35:21,800
I wasn't like that at all.

1642
02:35:24,640 --> 02:35:27,800
You were exactly like that, I thought I would pass out from boredom.

1643
02:35:28,120 --> 02:35:29,320
I could tell.

1644
02:35:30,320 --> 02:35:33,720
"Give us the best, most expensive one, man.

1645
02:35:33,760 --> 02:35:35,440
Take it out, come on.

1646
02:35:35,480 --> 02:35:37,240
We're not here to stay the night."

1647
02:35:37,240 --> 02:35:41,280
"Yes, that's the one. Bro, we'll buy that one and leave."

1648
02:35:43,440 --> 02:35:45,840
You're underselling me, I was worse than that.

1649
02:35:45,880 --> 02:35:47,080
My eyes were twitching.

1650
02:35:49,720 --> 02:35:51,320
But let me tell you something.

1651
02:35:51,360 --> 02:35:52,880
You got her an incredible present.

1652
02:35:52,920 --> 02:35:55,440
It's the first one you got her, it's good that it's meaningful.

1653
02:35:56,920 --> 02:35:58,200
Give me the key, I'll drive.

1654
02:35:58,200 --> 02:36:00,120
You must be tired after all that deliberation.

1655
02:36:55,800 --> 02:36:57,240
It's time I told her.

1656
02:37:05,520 --> 02:37:06,800
I'm coming.

1657
02:37:37,240 --> 02:37:39,240
Mercan, do you know where Demet is?

1658
02:37:40,160 --> 02:37:41,480
No, I don't.

1659
02:37:41,960 --> 02:37:43,920
I didn't see her around today.

1660
02:37:45,080 --> 02:37:46,360
Is there a problem?

1661
02:37:48,280 --> 02:37:49,800
We had an argument over Burak.

1662
02:37:50,760 --> 02:37:51,920
Why?

1663
02:37:52,200 --> 02:37:53,760
Is it because she was seeing him?

1664
02:37:54,920 --> 02:37:58,600
Yes, I overreacted a little bit. I got overly protective.

1665
02:38:00,200 --> 02:38:01,760
I think I broke her heart.

1666
02:38:01,800 --> 02:38:03,560
You're unbelievable, Nezir.

1667
02:38:03,600 --> 02:38:06,800
Burak is a nice guy, why shouldn't she see him?

1668
02:38:07,720 --> 02:38:09,280
I don't care if he's nice or not,

1669
02:38:10,960 --> 02:38:13,080
Still, I went to talk to her again.

1670
02:38:13,640 --> 02:38:15,440
She wasn't at her desk and her phone's off.

1671
02:38:24,760 --> 02:38:26,640
I'm afraid something happened to her.

1672
02:38:29,120 --> 02:38:31,080
You know, she's only just started

1673
02:38:31,120 --> 02:38:33,360
doing better after losing our parents.

1674
02:38:34,920 --> 02:38:37,000
I'm terrifed that something will go wrong again.

1675
02:38:38,560 --> 02:38:39,640
Hold on.

1676
02:38:47,800 --> 02:38:49,360
Her phone's still off.

1677
02:38:50,080 --> 02:38:51,200
Why meddle, Nezir?

1678
02:38:51,240 --> 02:38:53,600
Why did you come down on her so hard?

1679
02:38:53,600 --> 02:38:55,440
I'm angry with myself, too.

1680
02:38:59,080 --> 02:39:00,360
Let me ask Yaşar.

1681
02:39:00,360 --> 02:39:01,680
He must know something.

1682
02:39:21,280 --> 02:39:24,360
Have you seen Demet? Has she said anything to you?

1683
02:39:24,360 --> 02:39:26,040
No, she didn't say anything.

1684
02:39:26,040 --> 02:39:29,080
She was looking for her phone the last I saw her.

1685
02:39:29,600 --> 02:39:31,080
I don't know if she found it either.

1686
02:39:31,080 --> 02:39:32,880
And then, I saw her leaving.

1687
02:39:32,880 --> 02:39:35,760
She was a bit tense, she didn't say where she was going.

1688
02:39:36,720 --> 02:39:37,800
That's weird.

1689
02:39:44,440 --> 02:39:45,520
Okay, thanks.

1690
02:39:47,960 --> 02:39:50,200
Yaşar doesn't know where she is either.

1691
02:39:52,840 --> 02:39:55,040
I really came down on her, I broke her heart, Mercan.

1692
02:40:00,320 --> 02:40:01,720
What if she hurts herself?

1693
02:40:02,400 --> 02:40:04,880
Don't be ridiculous, Nezir. Why would she hurt herself?

1694
02:40:06,560 --> 02:40:07,560
Think harder.

1695
02:40:07,560 --> 02:40:10,600
Can you think of any place she may have gone?

1696
02:40:11,200 --> 02:40:13,560
You know she doesn't really have a sanctuary like that.

1697
02:40:14,280 --> 02:40:16,800
When she's upset, she either goes home or to the summer house.

1698
02:40:17,160 --> 02:40:18,320
Okay.

1699
02:40:18,640 --> 02:40:20,240
We'll check those places, then.

1700
02:40:20,520 --> 02:40:21,560
Okay.

1701
02:40:21,960 --> 02:40:23,360
Which one should we go to first?

1702
02:40:23,600 --> 02:40:26,000
We'll go one by one, let's not waste any time.

1703
02:40:26,200 --> 02:40:27,680
You go one place, I go to the other.

1704
02:40:27,920 --> 02:40:29,040
Yes, you're right.

1705
02:40:29,320 --> 02:40:31,000
I'm so worried, I can't think straight.

1706
02:40:31,800 --> 02:40:34,560
Then, I'll go home first and you'll go to the summer house.

1707
02:40:34,560 --> 02:40:35,760
We'll get in touch after.

1708
02:40:35,760 --> 02:40:37,640
Okay, let me get my bag and then, we'll leave.

1709
02:41:12,080 --> 02:41:14,880
You shouldn't. Since when do we let

1710
02:41:14,920 --> 02:41:17,560
each other know where we're going?

1711
02:41:17,600 --> 02:41:19,120
Am I missing something?

1712
02:41:22,640 --> 02:41:23,720
You're right.

1713
02:41:24,280 --> 02:41:25,520
There's no need.

1714
02:41:30,880 --> 02:41:31,920
Come on, let's go.

1715
02:41:42,680 --> 02:41:43,800
Mercan.

1716
02:41:44,360 --> 02:41:45,400
We'll find her, right?

1717
02:41:46,400 --> 02:41:48,120
Of course we will, don't worry.

1718
02:41:48,720 --> 02:41:51,360
We'll say "we worried for nothing." when we find her.

1719
02:41:53,480 --> 02:41:54,800
I will never upset her again.

1720
02:41:56,640 --> 02:41:59,960
Something like this doesn't have to happen just so we learn not to upset each other.

1721
02:42:01,560 --> 02:42:02,600
You're right.

1722
02:42:14,120 --> 02:42:15,400
I'll call you.

1723
02:43:12,240 --> 02:43:13,680
What's up?

1724
02:43:13,720 --> 02:43:15,480
What are you doing?

1725
02:43:18,560 --> 02:43:20,040
What do you think you're doing?

1726
02:43:20,920 --> 02:43:22,360
I just thought...

1727
02:43:22,400 --> 02:43:23,200
What?

1728
02:43:23,200 --> 02:43:25,640
What kind of a woman do you think I am? That's inappropriate.

1729
02:43:25,640 --> 02:43:27,640
I'm not an easy woman.

1730
02:43:27,680 --> 02:43:28,560
Do you hear me?

1731
02:43:28,600 --> 02:43:31,280
I'm an honorable woman who knows about chastity and decency.

1732
02:43:31,280 --> 02:43:33,000
If you step out of line again...

1733
02:43:33,040 --> 02:43:34,560
No, I won't. Okay.

1734
02:43:35,320 --> 02:43:37,280
Okay, I won't do it again.

1735
02:43:37,800 --> 02:43:39,280
I'm sorry.

1736
02:43:41,640 --> 02:43:45,480
I'm also a man of honor, I'm a decent man.

1737
02:43:45,480 --> 02:43:50,080
For example, I never miss a prayer on holidays.

1738
02:43:50,120 --> 02:43:52,360
I'm actually there before the Imam even gets there.

1739
02:43:53,280 --> 02:43:57,680
I was actually testing you to see if you would let it go on.

1740
02:43:57,720 --> 02:43:58,760
You were testing me?

1741
02:43:58,800 --> 02:43:59,760
Yes.

1742
02:44:03,720 --> 02:44:04,880
How are you?

1743
02:44:05,280 --> 02:44:06,640
I'm very angry.

1744
02:44:08,240 --> 02:44:09,280
At me, I suppose?

1745
02:44:09,320 --> 02:44:10,600
You're so quick-witted.

1746
02:44:14,480 --> 02:44:16,000
Well, take care.

1747
02:44:19,640 --> 02:44:21,960
I had some business to attend to anyway, so...

1748
02:44:26,800 --> 02:44:28,360
That was a close call, Berat.

1749
02:44:31,600 --> 02:44:32,880
She turned out to be a badass.

1750
02:44:33,400 --> 02:44:34,640
I have to give it to her.

1751
02:44:51,600 --> 02:44:53,200
Why are you here, mom?

1752
02:44:53,240 --> 02:44:54,360
Did something happen?

1753
02:44:57,440 --> 02:44:58,520
Yes, it did.

1754
02:45:00,280 --> 02:45:02,000
Something terrible, too.

1755
02:45:02,360 --> 02:45:07,400
Something terrible happened because you took this marriage thing too seriously.

1756
02:45:08,640 --> 02:45:11,280
You protected Mercan against us but,

1757
02:45:11,280 --> 02:45:14,400
she's dismissing you completely and seeing Nezir behind your back.

1758
02:45:16,600 --> 02:45:17,920
Mom.

1759
02:45:18,920 --> 02:45:20,840
Be careful what you say.

1760
02:45:22,760 --> 02:45:25,840
Son, I'm always careful with my words,

1761
02:45:25,840 --> 02:45:27,440
but are you?

1762
02:45:28,200 --> 02:45:30,600
Even if it's just a marriage on paper, she's still

1763
02:45:30,640 --> 02:45:33,000
your wife and I'm telling you she's betraying you.

1764
02:45:33,000 --> 02:45:34,600
Is this what you have to say?

1765
02:45:35,000 --> 02:45:36,920
Mom, you're stepping out of line.

1766
02:45:37,800 --> 02:45:39,000
You're out of line.

1767
02:45:41,040 --> 02:45:42,760
This is the only way you haven't tried.

1768
02:45:44,080 --> 02:45:45,400
I don't care about the line.

1769
02:45:45,800 --> 02:45:49,160
I'm not naive enough to trust my enemies like you are.

1770
02:45:49,160 --> 02:45:50,920
I can still see things clearly.

1771
02:45:51,640 --> 02:45:53,280
I'm having her followed.

1772
02:45:53,480 --> 02:45:54,840
That's why I came to you.

1773
02:45:56,640 --> 02:45:58,320
But if you insist on defending that

1774
02:45:58,320 --> 02:45:59,920
stranger instead of believing me...

1775
02:46:01,360 --> 02:46:02,880
Do you know where she is?

1776
02:46:03,400 --> 02:46:05,880
Where is that wife of yours you keep defending?

1777
02:46:10,360 --> 02:46:11,640
See for yourself.

1778
02:46:18,640 --> 02:46:21,000
They went out together, making the most of your absence.

1779
02:46:26,360 --> 02:46:28,800
They went to Nezir's summer house together.

1780
02:46:29,520 --> 02:46:32,400
Why would a married woman go to another man's house?

1781
02:46:32,920 --> 02:46:34,840
I'll leave that to your imagination.

1782
02:46:38,400 --> 02:46:39,480
Mercan.

1783
02:46:41,000 --> 02:46:42,280
Yes, Mercan.

1784
02:46:45,240 --> 02:46:47,720
We'll get photos from there as well, soon.

1785
02:46:48,240 --> 02:46:50,080
Although, you wouldn't believe those either.

1786
02:46:50,120 --> 02:46:52,360
You're dead set on defending that girl.

1787
02:46:53,560 --> 02:46:57,680
But if you don't believe me, go and see for yourself.

1788
02:46:58,240 --> 02:47:00,160
Of course, only if you have the guts.

1789
02:47:19,600 --> 02:47:22,400
Aslı? Ateş just left the company.

1790
02:47:35,840 --> 02:47:38,320
Mr. Haydar? You wanted to see me?

1791
02:47:39,800 --> 02:47:41,000
Go ahead, have a seat.

1792
02:47:41,880 --> 02:47:42,960
Have a seat.

1793
02:47:43,880 --> 02:47:44,920
Sit.

1794
02:47:46,800 --> 02:47:47,880
Yes, sir?

1795
02:47:49,320 --> 02:47:51,720
Berat, I've been watching you lately.

1796
02:47:51,760 --> 02:47:55,200
You seem really down, hanging your head all the time.

1797
02:47:56,200 --> 02:47:57,960
You obviously have a problem.

1798
02:47:59,600 --> 02:48:01,200
You know, we're all a family here.

1799
02:48:02,640 --> 02:48:04,600
You're like a son to me.

1800
02:48:04,600 --> 02:48:07,080
If there's anything I can do for you, just say the word.

1801
02:48:08,480 --> 02:48:11,280
Thank you, Mr. Haydar. That's very thoughtful of you.

1802
02:48:11,280 --> 02:48:13,320
But we don't have any problems, thankfully.

1803
02:48:14,360 --> 02:48:15,600
Berat.

1804
02:48:15,720 --> 02:48:18,600
I'm old enough to understand when something's wrong, Berat.

1805
02:48:19,520 --> 02:48:21,000
Don't deny it.

1806
02:48:21,680 --> 02:48:22,760
There's something.

1807
02:48:24,240 --> 02:48:26,560
Yes, I do have a problem. You're right, but,

1808
02:48:26,560 --> 02:48:28,440
I wouldn't want to impose on you my

1809
02:48:28,480 --> 02:48:30,680
problems that's why I didn't say anything.

1810
02:48:30,720 --> 02:48:33,040
It wouldn't be an imposition, don't worry.

1811
02:48:33,960 --> 02:48:35,640
Tell me, what's wrong?

1812
02:48:38,960 --> 02:48:41,080
It's financial, Mr. Haydar.

1813
02:48:41,760 --> 02:48:45,000
I've accumulated some debt out of necessity.

1814
02:48:45,040 --> 02:48:47,560
I have to pay it off as soon as possible but

1815
02:48:48,320 --> 02:48:50,240
it's not easy as you might guess.

1816
02:48:50,280 --> 02:48:53,840
I've been brooding and gloooming over what to do.

1817
02:48:54,960 --> 02:48:58,000
Berat, I thought it was something serious like an illness,

1818
02:49:00,120 --> 02:49:02,120
this is nothing to brood over.

1819
02:49:02,440 --> 02:49:04,880
Why would you get upset over money when I'm here?

1820
02:49:04,920 --> 02:49:08,400
A young man like you shouldn't go around with his head hanging low.

1821
02:49:08,400 --> 02:49:09,560
Keep your head high.

1822
02:49:09,840 --> 02:49:10,920
Stand tall.

1823
02:49:11,320 --> 02:49:12,320
There you go.

1824
02:49:12,360 --> 02:49:13,800
We'll figure it out, son.

1825
02:49:16,280 --> 02:49:18,120
Mr, Haydar, I wouldn't want

1826
02:49:18,160 --> 02:49:20,160
to impose on you like this.

1827
02:49:20,200 --> 02:49:23,960
It would be an imposition if you declined my help.

1828
02:49:24,360 --> 02:49:26,600
I'm practically your father.

1829
02:49:28,040 --> 02:49:29,400
You sure are, Mr. Haydar.

1830
02:49:29,440 --> 02:49:30,520
Let me kiss your hand.

1831
02:49:35,080 --> 02:49:36,600
Don't you worry, Mr. Haydar.

1832
02:49:36,640 --> 02:49:39,920
I'll work for you until I die and pay off my debt. I already...

1833
02:49:39,920 --> 02:49:41,200
Don't be ridiculous, Berat.

1834
02:49:41,240 --> 02:49:44,320
There's no need to work your entire life to slowly pay it off.

1835
02:49:45,360 --> 02:49:46,880
I wouldn't accept that,

1836
02:49:48,080 --> 02:49:49,960
it'd be as if I'm holding you hostage.

1837
02:49:51,920 --> 02:49:53,120
There's an easier way.

1838
02:49:55,880 --> 02:49:57,560
I'll help you out,

1839
02:49:58,680 --> 02:50:00,640
and you'll do some business for me.

1840
02:50:04,080 --> 02:50:07,280
And I'll erase that debt at once.

1841
02:50:08,400 --> 02:50:10,200
Both you and I will be set.

1842
02:50:18,960 --> 02:50:21,760
Okay, Mr. Haydar. It's obviously fine by me.

1843
02:50:25,440 --> 02:50:26,720
I'm at your order.

1844
02:50:28,200 --> 02:50:29,840
Not an order, just a wish.

1845
02:50:30,680 --> 02:50:31,720
Good.

1846
02:50:41,080 --> 02:50:43,360
Where are you, Demet? Where did you go?

1847
02:51:07,080 --> 02:51:10,080
What are you doing here? Weren't you going home?

1848
02:51:10,080 --> 02:51:13,640
I'd called my assistant to go and check home but she's not there.

1849
02:51:13,640 --> 02:51:15,920
So I hurried over here to see if she came here.

1850
02:51:15,960 --> 02:51:17,160
Is she here?

1851
02:51:17,200 --> 02:51:18,200
No.

1852
02:51:18,240 --> 02:51:20,280
I knocked but no one's here.

1853
02:51:22,640 --> 02:51:24,880
Why don't we go and check inside? Maybe she's sleeping.

1854
02:51:26,280 --> 02:51:27,720
I hope she's here.

1855
02:51:31,200 --> 02:51:34,080
Come on, go into the house. Come on.

1856
02:51:37,320 --> 02:51:38,840
I don't think she's here.

1857
02:51:38,880 --> 02:51:40,880
I knocked over and over again.

1858
02:51:40,920 --> 02:51:43,080
I called for her and looked through the windows.

1859
02:51:43,080 --> 02:51:44,840
But no one's here.

1860
02:51:45,320 --> 02:51:47,360
You go in and check if you'd like, I'll wait here.

1861
02:51:48,960 --> 02:51:50,600
What if she's passed out or something?

1862
02:51:52,240 --> 02:51:53,280
Nezir?

1863
02:52:04,280 --> 02:52:05,640
Are you okay?

1864
02:52:06,200 --> 02:52:07,360
I'm okay.

1865
02:52:07,360 --> 02:52:08,400
Are you sure?

1866
02:52:08,440 --> 02:52:09,600
Yes, I'm fine.

1867
02:52:10,120 --> 02:52:11,760
I just felt dizzy.

1868
02:52:14,480 --> 02:52:16,400
I'll go and check inside.

1869
02:52:16,440 --> 02:52:20,200
I grew really worried. You go and check, I'll wait here.

1870
02:52:42,320 --> 02:52:43,600
Mom.

1871
02:52:43,600 --> 02:52:45,000
Did you call me?

1872
02:52:45,360 --> 02:52:46,880
Have a seat.

1873
02:52:46,880 --> 02:52:49,280
Okay, I'll sit. Is there something wrong?

1874
02:52:50,560 --> 02:52:51,960
I told you to sit.

1875
02:52:56,840 --> 02:52:59,080
Ms. Binnaz? Did you call me?

1876
02:52:59,120 --> 02:53:01,240
You go and sit over there.

1877
02:53:02,720 --> 02:53:03,720
Okay.

1878
02:53:17,400 --> 02:53:19,240
I've tried telling you nicely,

1879
02:53:19,240 --> 02:53:20,920
haven't I?

1880
02:53:21,920 --> 02:53:23,200
I told you to end it.

1881
02:53:23,200 --> 02:53:24,240
Didn't I?

1882
02:53:28,600 --> 02:53:30,600
Did you listen? No.

1883
02:53:30,600 --> 02:53:31,920
You didn't.

1884
02:53:32,440 --> 02:53:34,360
But mom, I've told you,

1885
02:53:34,360 --> 02:53:35,600
we love each other.

1886
02:53:35,600 --> 02:53:38,280
Ms. Binnaz, we have serious intentions. We...

1887
02:53:38,280 --> 02:53:39,800
Shush.

1888
02:53:45,680 --> 02:53:49,840
If you won't listen, you don't leave me any other choice.

1889
02:54:00,320 --> 02:54:03,240
Either Çiçek goes back to Trabzon or you pack up

1890
02:54:03,280 --> 02:54:06,120
your stuff and go back to your hometown, Malik.

1891
02:54:17,520 --> 02:54:21,080
So it ends either way.

1892
02:54:25,000 --> 02:54:27,240
Çiçek and Malik together is too much for this house.

1893
02:54:27,280 --> 02:54:29,440
One of you will leave.

1894
02:54:29,480 --> 02:54:32,400
You should talk and decide between the two of you

1895
02:54:33,120 --> 02:54:34,560
which one of you should leave.

1896
02:54:36,720 --> 02:54:38,280
You left me no other choice.

1897
02:54:39,280 --> 02:54:40,440
That's it.

1898
02:55:10,400 --> 02:55:11,640
She's not here, is she?

1899
02:55:11,640 --> 02:55:12,840
No.

1900
02:55:13,640 --> 02:55:15,800
Let's go, then. Let's keep looking.

1901
02:55:22,160 --> 02:55:24,000
You need to get her into the house.

1902
02:55:24,000 --> 02:55:26,800
Stall her a little bit, Ateş will be here in a moment.

1903
02:55:26,840 --> 02:55:27,920
Is it Demet?

1904
02:55:29,080 --> 02:55:30,280
No, it's not.

1905
02:55:30,320 --> 02:55:31,200
It's my assistant.

1906
02:55:31,240 --> 02:55:33,600
She's letting me know Demet hasn't come home.

1907
02:55:39,120 --> 02:55:42,960
I'm not doing well, Mercan. Where is she?

1908
02:55:45,040 --> 02:55:48,120
She might have gone to a cafe near your house.

1909
02:55:48,160 --> 02:55:50,400
Maybe she justs want to be alone.

1910
02:55:52,760 --> 02:55:54,480
Could we wait a little longer?

1911
02:55:54,520 --> 02:55:56,080
Maybe she'll come.

1912
02:55:57,640 --> 02:55:59,320
I'm not sure what to think.

1913
02:56:01,480 --> 02:56:02,760
You know what?

1914
02:56:03,600 --> 02:56:05,520
You go and wait inside.

1915
02:56:05,560 --> 02:56:07,480
I'll wait in the car.

1916
02:56:07,840 --> 02:56:09,840
Don't be ridiculous. There's no need for that.

1917
02:56:09,840 --> 02:56:11,280
You do as I say.

1918
02:56:12,040 --> 02:56:15,920
Mercan, I'm still dizzy anyway. It's not like I'll drive in this state.

1919
02:56:24,400 --> 02:56:25,480
Come on.

1920
02:57:05,960 --> 02:57:07,040
Ateş.

1921
02:57:15,440 --> 02:57:16,920
What are you doing here?

1922
02:57:22,400 --> 02:57:24,000
What are you doing with this man?
